name: PRINCE HALL COLONIAL PARK DAY CARE CENTER
PUSTEBLUME GERMAN LANGUAGE PRESCHOOLS AND AFTER-SCHOOL PROGAMS
detail:
Pusteblume International Preschool provides children with a fun and community-oriented multicultural environment where instruction in the German and Spanish language serves as a catalyst for the development of each child’s unique cultural identity.

Our licensed, native-speaking, early childhood educators focus on providing quality instruction in a warm and nurturing setting that cultivates the growth and development of your child. Music, movement, literacy, and visual arts are an integral part of the preschool curriculum.

We welcome families with children from 2 to 5 years of age of all international backgrounds who are interested in having their child learn either German or Spanish as a second language.  And for older children, please check out our range of afterschool language immersion activities for children ages 6 to 12 years of age!

Pusteblume International Preschool is directed by Friends of the German International School of New York, Inc., a non-profit, 501(c)(3) corporation.

name: RED BALLOON DAY CARE CENTER
detail: The Red Balloon strives to be a model of exemplary early childhood education practices. We partner with families to create a safe nurturing environment where children are encouraged to reach their full potential while planting the seed for lifelong learning.

name: RENAISSANCE VILLAGE
detail:
Renaissance Village Family Learning Center has as its focus the entire family, providing Montessori Nurseries for children and other activities that enhance well being and parenting skills for adults. Our goal is to help create and support happy, secure families. Our mission is to support the parent as the child’s primary teacher.
 
Renaissance Village is a member of American Montessori Society and licensed by New York City Department of Health.
 
The founder of Renaissance is Dr. Tatjana Matano, fourth generation educator originally from Eastern Europe. Tatjana has over twenty years of experience in education as University teacher, trainer in whole brain and accelerated learning for adults and as an early childhood educator. In 2001, after the birth of her second child, she started a special, enriched Nursery program in Hudson Heights in Manhattan which evolved into a Montessori center by 2007. As a mother of two children she herself knows the struggles of parenting and the importance of choosing the right educational environment during early years.
 
Tatjana has assembled a team of devoted teachers and assistants who share her own dedication to the early childhood as the most important period for the fulfillment of one’s potential and who also share her dedication to parenting community as a whole. The Education Director and Head Teacher of Renaissance Village is Ms. Jean Caswell, a veteran of Montessori teaching with over 35 yrs of experience. Ms. Olga Schmukler is her partner, an early childhood educator with outstanding talents in the areas of Music and Art and with over 20 yrs of experience in the classroom. She combines Russian Music pedagogy with Montessori principles . Our program has two more teachers and two assistants who make sure the Montessori philosophy of respect and trust in the child is present throughout the day and beyond the class time.
 
Dr. Matano and Ms. Caswell are dedicated to continuous and thorough training of the entire staff in the principles of Montessori work. They also offer parenting workshops and have developed a nine month program (sept-june) for families entitled “The Joyful Family” which elaborates on all the aspects of family life through the lens of Montessori approach. In addition, the Assistants are trained in Health and Safety, CPR, First Aid, Control of Infectious Disease, Child Abuse Prevention and Food Protection.

name: RENANIM MANHATTAN, INC.
detail: RENANIM is our name. In Hebrew "Renanim" means happiness. We offer an excellent preschool education in an atmosphere of happiness and joy for children 18 months to 6 years old. We started in Israel and now operate in Manhattan and in Riverdale. With over 45 years of experience, we have a lot to offer your child.  RENANIM provides a caring, nurturing and stimulating environment where your child will learn through developmentally appropriate activities. We strive to build confidence and self-esteem, fostering active learning through exploration and inquiry. Our classes are organized according to age. While the programs for the younger children differ from those for the older children, the curriculum for all of the children is designed to encourage them to participate in creative activities, and activities that promote language and speech.

name: RHINELANDER CHILDREN'S AID SOCEITY
detail:
The Rhinelander Nursery School, located in the Yorkville neighborhood, is a community of families and teachers who are committed to fostering an early love of learning and school.
(Ages 2 1/2-5)

At Rhinelander, the emphasis is on nurturing the needs of each child within a group setting. Our child-centered approach supports language and literacy development, social and emotional growth and creative thinking. We believe learning should be fun and employ a play-based, multi-sensory approach. Children develop their skills and senses differently — some need to "see it"; some need to "hear it"; others need to "try it". Our multi-faceted lesson plans address diverse learning styles.

name: RITA GOLD EARLY CHILDHOOD CENTER
detail:
Founded in 1982 by Leslie Williams and Annette Axtmann as the Center for Infants and Parents (CIP), the Center has long been providing quality early care and education for the youngest children and their families and professional preparation for graduate students whose studies focus on infancy. Over the years and with the support of Teachers College, the Center has grown from one part-time infant toddler room, primarily serving children of TC graduate students, into a more comprehensive service program providing full-time and year-round care and education.

We now serve children from 2 months through 5 years of age whose families are currently affiliated with Columbia University as students, staff, or faculty. Early care and education is provided in three rooms, each with a mixed-age group of children. Adaptability to meet a wide variety of developmental needs is built into the program. The Center's growth and development has also been supported through the gifts of many kind and generous donors. We are grateful to Rita and Herbert Gold for their support of our most recent expansion.

name: RIVER PARK NURSERY SCHOOL AND KINDERGARTEN
detail:
For more than 30 years, River Park Nursery School has been nurturing the young children of the Upper West Side community - preparing them with the skills necessary to move confidently between the family and the wider world of learning in society.

Our core goal is the individual growth and the development of the whole child - creatively, socially, emotionally, and intellectually. We meet each child at his or her own level and pace, then guide and build from there. Through this personal approach a sense of trust, dignity and self-respect is strengthened.

name: RIVERSIDE MONTESSORI SCHOOL
detail:
Our mission is to nurture children in a child-centered setting that fosters the growth of confident, caring, and successful children. Each of our three preschools in Manhattan’s Upper West side provides a gentle, secure environment. Each helps children learn how to learn. And each lays a firm foundation for building a dynamic community of life-long learners.

Twin Parks Montessori is the largest accredited Montessori program in Manhattan and the only Infant Toddler Program in New York State to be accredited by both the American Montessori Society (AMS) and the Middle States Commission on Elementary Schools (MSCES). Twin Parks Montessori Schools enjoy membership in the New York State Association of Independent Schools (NYSAIS), the Independent School Admission Association of Greater New York (ISAAGNY) and the Parents League, as well as affiliate schools of Columbia University.
business hours:
Mon - Thu: 8:00 am - 6:00 pm
Fri: 8:00 am - 5:00 pm

name: ROOSEVELT ISLAND DAY NURSERY
detail:
The Roosevelt Island Day Nursery (RIDN) is an international school whose population reflects the rich ethnic, cultural and racial diversity of the Roosevelt Island community. The Day Nursery provides infant, toddler, and preschool programs for children ages 3 months through 5 years.

RIDN is located in two sites offering views of the East River the Queensboro Bridge and the NYC skyline. Each school provides opportunities for year round outdoor play in well equipped playgrounds and beautiful green lawns.

RIDN has been serving the community for over 30 years and welcomes visitors to see and learn more about our many programs.

name: ROOSEVELT ISLAND DAY NURSERY
detail:
The Roosevelt Island Day Nursery (RIDN) is an international school whose population reflects the rich ethnic, cultural and racial diversity of the Roosevelt Island community. The Day Nursery provides infant, toddler, and preschool programs for children ages 3 months through 5 years.

RIDN is located in two sites offering views of the East River the Queensboro Bridge and the NYC skyline. Each school provides opportunities for year round outdoor play in well equipped playgrounds and beautiful green lawns.

RIDN has been serving the community for over 30 years and welcomes visitors to see and learn more about our many programs.

name: SEPHARDIC ACADEMY OF MANHATTAN
detail: With an unwavering commitment to the rich traditions and culture we treasure, SAM creates a warm and nurturing atmosphere with an unwavering commitment to enrich a child's social, academic, cognitive and spiritual development.At SAM, we believe in educating the whole child and offering them a warm and nurturing environment in which to thrive in their early, formative years.

name: SEVENTH AVENUE CENTER FOR FAMILY SERVICES HEAD START
SHALOM YELADIM EARLY CHILDHOOD CENTER.
detail:
Our mission is to provide each child with a safe and stimulating environment.

The well- rounded curriculum encourages the students to reach their full potential in emotional, social, physical, academic and spiritual areas of life.

In addition, we strive to provide our parents with a secure and convenient place, with a feeling of home and family.

name: SMARTER TODDLER
detail: At Smarter Toddler we strive to have a positive and welcoming environment. We provide a relaxed admissions process, remarkable teachers, placing value on diversity, and accommodating children who have needs requiring additional attention.

name: SMARTER TODDLER NURSERY & PRESCHOOL
detail: At Smarter Toddler we strive to have a positive and welcoming environment. We provide a relaxed admissions process, remarkable teachers, placing value on diversity, and accommodating children who have needs requiring additional attention.

name: SOCIETY OF THIRD STREET MUSIC SCHOOL SETTLEMENT PRESCHOOL
ST. IGNATIUS LAYOLA DAY NURSERY
detail: St. Ignatius Loyola Day Nursery is a home away from home where faith, love, and knowledge form the cornerstones of a rigorous child-centered curriculum. In a bright, safe, beautiful townhouse on East 84th Street, children develop a strong sense of self, an abiding respect for others, and a lifelong love of learning.

name: ST. THOMAS MORE PLAY GROUP
detail:
Our primary objective is to provide a warm, responsive, and supportive atmosphere for each child to begin his social and academic journey through life. It is our belief that a child’s first school experience should be his strongest in terms of trust and security in his teachers and surroundings. Our caring and relaxed approach provides each child with a positive foundation enabling him to cope with a wide variety of future educational environments and pressures. We want children to leave the Play Group with strong self-esteem and a feeling of confidence and enthusiasm for learning.

We accommodate each child in the Play Group as totally unique in his emotional needs, group adaptation capabilities, and skills readiness. Rudimentary socialization skills are an important emphasis in our program, but not at the expense of the child’s sense of self or overall happiness. Individual differences and “stages” are quickly perceived and respected. Our program and facilities provide a rich environment for learning and growth. A wide variety of activities and materials encourage the child’s emotional, intellectual, social and physical development. Individual and group projects spark curiosity and stimulate the children to observe, experiment freely, become problem solvers, and acquire basic skills without the fear of failure.

name: ST.BARTHOLOMEW COMMUNITY PRE-SCHOOL
detail: St. Bart's educational philosophy is based on fostering a love of learning, while celebrating and embracing each child’s uniqueness. We are committed to providing an environment where children’s curiosity is encouraged.

name: STEPHEN WISE EARLY CHILDHOOD CENTER
detail: The SWFS Balfour Brickner Early Childhood Center (ECC) carries on Stephen Wise Free Synagogue’s long tradition of educating young children. In 1949, the Synagogue opened what was then called the Nursery School and Kindergarten, where children learned through creative play in a Jewish environment. Now, over 60 years later, the ECC continues to educate and inspire the youngest members of the Stephen Wise community.

name: SUNSHINE DAY CARE
detail:
Sunshine Daycare provides educational infant, toddler, and preschool programs to children ages six weeks through 5 years of age. Our experienced, nurturing staff is passionate about showing children, as early as possible, that learning isn’t a chore— it’s a lot of fun!

An Exceptional Early Childhood Center
    As a matter of convenience for working parents, we are open from 7:30a.m. to 6:30p.m., Monday through Friday.
    Our age-specific curriculum is designed to stimulate and cultivate the student’s intellect in a fun way that makes them want to come in every day.
    We believe that a healthy mind can’t be attained without a healthy body, so we provide a nutritious breakfast, lunch and snack every day.
    Sunshine pre-school programs have been servicing diverse families and communities in Brooklyn, Manhattan and the Bronx since 2004. Our universal goal is to offer affordable family solutions for parents while inspiring a passion for knowledge in children at a young age.
    We are proud of our affordable, top-quality Pre-K programs, so as a means to extend our services to a broad range of financial abilities, we accept all New York City vouchers issued by HRA and ACD.

Sunshine’s Philosophy
    We are an Early Childhood center that serves not as a mere daycare center, but as a place where your child can begin to build the foundation for a life of educational pursuits.
    We treat every activity as a chance for your child to learn and grow. No activity is without an enriching purpose behind it.
    We feel that by keeping your children intellectually and socially stimulated, they will hit the ground running while attending school in their later years.
    Communication between our parents, children and faculty is extremely important to us, so we have an “open door policy” to ensure every question, concern, or issue is addressed.

name: T.R. LITTLE PEOPLE
detail: The House of Little People is a family-owned, multi-generation, early childhood learning facility founded in 1976. We assist in the growth and development of the total child. Our pioneering, personalized approach, along with the compassion and the establishing of trust (Child and Teacher) is quite unique and the results provide your child with the ability to be prepared to the meet the challenges of kindergarten and beyond.

name: TEMPLE ISRAEL EARLY CHILDHOOD LEARNING CENTER
THE MONTESSORI AT FLATIRON
detail: The Montessori Schools in Flatiron & SoHo provide an engaging early childhood education program built upon the classical methods of Maria Montessori. Our school puts children ages 2 to 5 years old on a path that embraces creativity, builds self-awareness and helps them develop the academic skills, physical tools and personal confidence necessary for lifelong success.

name: THE PARK PRESCHOOL LTD.
detail:
The Park Preschool and The Barclay Street School serve children from two years of age to five years of age. The belief that children learn through play is the guiding principle The Park Preschool was founded on and has maintained since its inception in 1989. Over the past 20 years we have developed a philosophy and curriculum that nurtures each child’s potential growth and development and instills in the children a love for learning and a desire for discovery and challenge. With the fall 2008 opening of The Barclay Street School, we will be able to share this aspiration for knowledge with our growing community.

The teachers at The Park Preschool and The Barclay Street School will foster each child’s independent thinking skills and thus help the children become self-confident as they become sensitive to the world around them. We give them freedom, let them try, let them fail, encourage them, let them succeed, and rejoice with them!

name: THE ACORN SCHOOL
detail: The educational approach at The Acorn School provides children with an exciting learning environment that is both integrated and self-stimulating. With guidance from our teachers, the children engage in both independent and collaborative exploration. The learning and growth process is encouraged via "hands on" experiences that foster a child's innate sense of creativity and curiosity. Our goal is to have a positive impact on each child's social, emotional, physical and intellectual growth in an atmosphere of individual respect and love of The Acorn School community.

name: THE BARCLAY STREET SCHOOL LTD.
detail:
The Barclay Street School and The Park Preschool  serve children from two years of age to five years of age.  The belief that children learn through play is the guiding principle The Park Preschool was founded on and has maintained since its inception in 1989.  Over the years we have developed a philosophy and curriculum that nurtures each child’s potential growth and development and instills in the children a love for learning and a desire for discovery and challenge.  With the fall 2008 opening of The Barclay Street School, we are now able to share this aspiration for knowledge with our growing community.

The teachers at The Barclay Street School and The Park Preschool will foster each child’s independent thinking skills and thus help the children become self-confident as they become sensitive to the world around them. We give them freedom, let them try, let them fail, encourage them, let them succeed, and rejoice with them!

name: THE BRICK CHURCH SCHOOL
detail:
Founded by The Brick Presbyterian Church in 1940, the Brick Church School is a community where children, their families, teachers and staff of the School and Church are valued and respected. It is a place where teachers as well as children are continually learning with the School’s strong support. The family and School are viewed as partners in the education process. As an integral part of the life and mission of the Church, the School conducts a weekly chapel service for the children.

Children of all racial, ethnic, religious, and economic backgrounds, and family configurations are welcomed as part of the School’s and Church’s commitment to diversity and inclusiveness. In an atmosphere of warmth and mutual respect, teachers help children become productive members of a community of learners.

The School recognizes that play is the work of young children. It strives to address children’s different learning styles by engaging in project work that is grounded in topics of interest to children as well as teaching basic skills, and by maintaining a balance between teacher direction and freedom of choice for the child.

The Brick Church School’s ultimate goal is for its students to leave the School as happy, self-confident individuals, mindful of God’s love, accepting of themselves and others, filled with curiosity and joy in learning.

name: THE BROWNSTONE SCHOOL AND DAY CARE
detail: Since 1963, The Brownstone School has welcomed children and families into a nurturing community. Our warm and inspiring educators encourage children to explore, experiment, collaborate and create through directed play. Our school fosters the social, emotional and educational skills essential for a joyful approach to learning. The Brownstone School supports an educational philosophy which holds that children are continually striving to attain emotional, social, intellectual and physical maturity. The teaching staff are trained to provide appropriate experiences and activities in a suitable environment to help children achieve those goals. We also believe that children become successful lifelong learners when they are helped to develop a strong sense of identity and self-worth. In the process of helping children develop, grow and achieve, teachers take into account broad developmental differences due to age, individual rates of development, personality, learning styles, cultural backgrounds, and the ways in which each family functions. It is recognized that the family is the main source of security and identity for the child.

name: THE CHILDREN'S AID SOCIETY - PS 5 HEAD START
detail: The Children’s Aid Society helps children in poverty to succeed and thrive. We do this by providing comprehensive supports to children and their families in targeted high-needs New York City neighborhoods.

name: THE CHILDREN'S LEARNING CENTER AT HUNTER COLLEGE
THE CHURCH OF THE EPIPHANY DAY SCHOOL
detail: The Church of the Epiphany Day School is a nurturing and inviting pre-school on Manhattan’s Upper Eastside that welcomes children of all faiths, ages 2 through 5 years of age. The Day School community consists of families, faculty and staff who represent a diverse range of ethnicities, nationalities, creeds and socio-economic backgrounds. Since our founding in 2004, The Church of the Epiphany Day School has been serving its community with an inspiring program that respects children’s ideas as being meaningful and important. With a strong focus on the importance of learning through creative endeavors and supporting socialization through play, our dedicated faculty embraces each child’s unique personality and learning style. We are committed to promoting the emotional, social, cognitive and physical growth of each child and we strive to enhance each child’s sense of self by understanding and appreciating them and his or her efforts in all areas.

name: THE EDUCATIONAL ALLIANCE HEAD START @ PS 142
detail: We are a community-based organization offering a wide range of programs that integrate education, social services, arts and recreation throughout Downtown Manhattan. We are a Jewish organization, serving people of diverse ethnic, religious and socio-economic backgrounds who live, work and learn in our neighborhoods. We strive to nourish the total person, strengthen family connections and build inclusive communities.

name: THE EPISCOPAL SCHOOL IN THE CITY OF NEW YORK
detail:
The mission of The Episcopal School is to provide a traditional early childhood program. We strive to help each child develop socially, emotionally, physically and intellectually and to fulfill his or her potential in a structured, nurturing environment.

We are committed to maintaining a healthy balance between a noncompetitive, supportive environment and a challenging experience through which children develop a strong sense of values and a positive image of themselves and of school.

Our students are encouraged to be curious, independent and responsible, and to enjoy learning. We seek, in a Judeo-Christian setting, to give children the best possible preparation for their ongoing education, as well as for a rewarding life.

name: THE FAMILY ANNEX
detail: Children are rich with theories and ideas. The Family Annex classes have a co-created curriculum. This is a balance between the adults and children. Children are challenged and provoked in a positive way. The curriculum that evolves from this co-creation is one that is project based emanating from children’s thoughts, questions and hypotheses about the world around them.   The role of the teacher is to encourage critical thinking on the part of the children, to encourage children to ask questions and to be a researcher with the children. The teachers are also observers who try to understand the way the world looks to children. The teachers carefully plan questions and explorations that will stimulate the children’s innate curiosity and love for learning. The teachers are active observers working to see how best to inspire the children and support their learning.

name: THE GODDARD SCHOOL
detail: Welcome! Our goal is to be a resource to you and your family, while creating a community where parents can share information and learn from each other. The Goddard School uses the most current, academically endorsed methods to ensure that children have fun while learning the skills they need for long-term success in school and in life. Our talented teachers also collaborate with parents to nurture children into respectful, confident and joyful learners.

name: THE HOUSE OF LITTLE PEOPLE, INC.
detail: The House of Little People is a family-owned, multi-generation, early childhood learning facility founded in 1976. We assist in the growth and development of the total child. Our pioneering, personalized approach, along with the compassion and the establishing of trust (Child and Teacher) is quite unique and the results provide your child with the ability to be prepared to the meet the challenges of kindergarten and beyond.

name: THE HOUSE OF LITTLE PEOPLE, TOO
detail: The House of Little People is a family-owned, multi-generation, early childhood learning facility founded in 1976. We assist in the growth and development of the total child. Our pioneering, personalized approach, along with the compassion and the establishing of trust (Child and Teacher) is quite unique and the results provide your child with the ability to be prepared to the meet the challenges of kindergarten and beyond.

name: THE INTERNATIONAL PRESCHOOL
detail: The preschool years are a crucial window in a child’s academic, social and cultural development. In the few years spent at The International Preschools, a child will develop not only academic skills but also social skills and cultural attitudes. At The International Preschools, where English language learners are welcomed and supported, children and families from New York City and all over the world share their cultures and gain a sense of international awareness through mutual understanding and respect. Through play, we promote the cognitive, emotional, social and physical growth of each child in a nurturing atmosphere. With schools in multiple Manhattan neighborhoods children may attend school close to home while their families are part of a large and vibrant parent and faculty network. The size of The International Preschools allows us to be a laboratory for curriculum development, including a rich variety of specialty activities based on early childhood educational research and good practices.

name: THE MADISON AVENUE PRESBYTERIAN CHURCH DAY SCHOOL
THE MONTESSORI FAMILY SCHOOL OF MANHATTAN
THE MONTESSORI SCHOOL OF NEW YORK INTERNATIONAL
detail:
The Montessori School of New York International has was founded in 1970. We offer programs for students from two to 14 years of age.

As an authentic Montessori school, our curriculum and programs are designed to build a strong foundation in academics, as well as social, emotional, physical and moral development. This approach encourages a child’s independence, self-motivation, and decision-making skills.

Our Montessori and state certified teachers receive continuing education and participate in ongoing training throughout the year. Supplemental teachers specialize in dance, music, foreign languages, and art. We maintain teacher to student ratios as required by the state of New York.

Our classrooms are designed to stimulate the child’s natural curiosity to explore the world around them. The classrooms are fully equipped with age-appropriate Montessori materials and our outdoor area is spacious with an engaging playground. Children can organize their own free play, get together and use the half basketball court, or participate in other organized sporting activities.

name: THE RIVERSIDE CHURCH WEEKDAY SCHOOL
detail: The Riverside Church Weekday School has a rich, eighty-three year history of educating children to change the world. Established in 1930, Weekday is a non-denominational, early childhood school serving children ages two through five in a joy-filled, nurturing setting committed to addressing the unique needs of young children. Our school’s mission, inspired by the spirit of the Riverside Church mission, is to nurture an awareness of diversity, mutual respect, compassion, empathy and community.

name: THE ROCKEFELLER UNIVERSITY CHILD & FAMILY CENTER
detail:
The Child and Family Center (CFC) is located on the campus of the Rockefeller University in the GSR and Sophie Fricke buildings. Childcare and education at the CFC is available to families affiliated with Rockefeller University. Parents need to apply far ahead of the time that they will need childcare and education for their child as there is great demand for the spaces. Our families reflect the multicultural dimension of science. They come from all over the world to study and work here. We have as many as 26 different languages represented in our student body. Our teaching staff is also multinational. Many of the teachers are bi-lingual.

The parents' labs and offices are close by allowing them, when they have the time, to visit their children in the center. Some parents like to have lunch with their children, others like to come after nap time for a visit. This means that for the child and parents they don't have to be separated 8 or 10 hours a day; they can see each other during the day. The CFC is open 50 weeks a year from 8:30 to 6:00, Monday through Friday. We close the week between Christmas and New Year's, when the University is closed and for the week before Labor Day for the teachers' work week.

name: THE SAUL AND CAROLE NURSERY SCHOOL AT THE J C C IN MANHATTAN
detail: The Saul and Carole Zabar Nursery School at The JCC in Manhattan is a progressive preschool that embraces families from all backgrounds and cultivates a connection to Jewish values and tradition. Teachers work collaboratively to create environments and experiences that spark wonder and creativity, build confidence and skills, allow children to explore materials, and encourage a questioning mind. Families are partners in the work that we do, joining with children and teachers to celebrate Jewish life and learning. We are caretakers of each other, our school community, our city, and our planet.

name: THE WASHINGTON MARKET SCHOOL
detail: We are a non-profit, non-sectarian Preschool and Kindergarten for children ages 2 to 6 located in the heart of New York City's Tribeca neighborhood. The goals of our school are to develop children's self-confidence, independence, and concentration, and to nurture their inherent interest in learning and creativity.

name: THE WASHINGTON MARKET SCHOOL
detail: We are a non-profit, non-sectarian Preschool and Kindergarten for children ages 2 to 6 located in the heart of New York City's Tribeca neighborhood. The goals of our school are to develop children's self-confidence, independence, and concentration, and to nurture their inherent interest in learning and creativity.

name: THE WILLIAM WOODARD JR. NURSERY SCHOOL
detail:
In every school, but particularly in an early childhood program, the basic philosophy is the inspiration for and foundation of, the specific curriculum. The educational goal of The William Woodward Jr. Nursery School is to provide a setting in which children are nurtured in all areas of development - social, emotional, intellectual and physical.

Children are active learners and learn from their experiences. From the moment of birth, they are experiencing and discovering the world through their senses. In cheerful, child centered classrooms, children are encouraged to learn by exploring, trying, and doing. Teachers trained in early childhood education act as facilitators, guiding children to learn through play. At Woodward, we help prepare children both for the academics and for life, by fostering in them a healthy ego and sense of self, an inner discipline, respect, and empathy for others, gradually increasing independence, and an awareness that they are an important part of the community.

Our school community is national and international and we work together to understand and appreciate our unique differences. The staff is skilled in developing communication between native English-speaking children, and children whose primary language is other than English. The diversity of families at Woodward enriches us all.

name: TOMPKINS HALL NURSERY & CHILDCARE CENTER INFANT/TODDLER PROGRAM
detail:
Our school strives to integrate each child's individual development with the experience of belonging to a group. Through creative play with a variety of materials, children develop awareness of themselves and the world around them. We help children to verbalize their feelings and communicate with adults and with peers. Problem-solving, with materials and in social interactions, is integrated into all our daily experiences.

Tompkins Hall is home to a Childcare Center that comprises a Infant/Toddler Room for children up to 19 months and a Twos Room for children 20 months to 2 years, 8 months, and to a Nursery School (preschool) for children 2 years, 9 months to 5 years. In addition, our roof serves as a playground and an organic garden.

name: TRIBECA COMMUNITY SCHOOL
detail: Yo Re Mi is a musical yoga program for children. In each fun-filled session, we journey to exotic destinations using our bodies, voices, and imaginations. We collaboratively explore nature, geography, culture, rhythm, dance, songwriting and playing instruments. Through Yo Re Mi's unique integration of yoga and music, children develop self-confidence, focus, communication, and mind-body awareness.

name: TRINITY PARISH PRESCHOOL AND NURSERY
detail:
Since 1982, Trinity Preschool and Nursery has provided high-quality childcare in the heart of New York City's financial district for children aged three months to five years. We are members of the Independent Schools Admissions Association of Greater New York (ISAAGNY) and the National Association of Episcopal Schools (NAES).

We offer a full-day program, with hours of operation from 8am to 6pm. Children can attend school five days, three days, or two days per week, subject to availability. We have eleven classrooms at our downtown New York location.

As early childhood professionals, our teachers sustain high standards of child-care practices. We use a variety of teaching strategies to enhance learning and development, and an appropriately challenging and safe environment is provided for Infants and Toddlers to explore and manipulate.

Children are encouraged to learn and grow at their own rates and in their own ways. Our teachers focus on the whole child - social, emotional, intellectual, physical, and spiritual - within a structure that allows for some natural flexibility.

name: TWIN PARKS MONTESSORI SCHOOL
detail:
Our mission is to nurture children in a child-centered setting that fosters the growth of confident, caring, and successful children. Each of our three preschools in Manhattan’s Upper West side provides a gentle, secure environment. Each helps children learn how to learn. And each lays a firm foundation for building a dynamic community of life-long learners.

Twin Parks Montessori is the largest accredited Montessori program in Manhattan and the only Infant Toddler Program in New York State to be accredited by both the American Montessori Society (AMS) and the Middle States Commission on Elementary Schools (MSCES). Twin Parks Montessori Schools enjoy membership in the New York State Association of Independent Schools (NYSAIS), the Independent School Admission Association of Greater New York (ISAAGNY) and the Parents League, as well as affiliate schools of Columbia University.
business hours:
Mon - Thu: 8:00 am - 6:00 pm
Fri: 8:00 am - 5:00 pm

name: U F B C O CHILD DEVELOPMENT CENTER
UNION CARVER CHILDREN'S CENTER
detail:
Our mission is to provide children with a well-rounded program that includes all aspects of learning. Children receive individualized instruction that includes cognitive, social, creative and physical development.

We serve 500 children and their families in seven childcare and Head Start centers. Teachers in our pre-school program assist children ages two to five in a stimulating social and educational environment. We operate a Universal Pre-Kindergarten program with Community School District 4/Region 9.

Union Settlement's Family Child Care Network prepares community members to establish and run their own home-based child care businesses. Our providers care for children ages 8 weeks to 12 years in an educationally stimulating home-based setting. Union Settlement Child Care programs operate from 8AM to 6PM and our Head Start programs operate from 8AM to 4:30PM. Both programs are open year round.

All child care centers and home care providers are licensed by the Department of Health and provide hot, nutritious meals to all participants. Because parent involvement is essential to child development, we encouraged and welcome parents in all aspects of our programs.

name: UNIVERSITY PLAZA NURSERY SCHOOL
detail: Our goal is to provide a nursery school experience that builds on the natural curiosity each child is born with. We foster the learning process by encouraging children to explore their own interests in a warm, caring and child-centered setting. Children are supported as they learn important social skills through play and relationships within the classroom community. It is important to us that children leave UPNS with the social, emotional and academic skills to succeed in Kindergarten.

name: UPPER MANHATTAN MENTAL HEALTH CENTER THERAPEUTIC PRE-SCHOOL
VANDERBILT Y M C A E C C I I I
VICTORIA CHILDREN'S GROUP
detail:
Being a family-owned and operated school, we’re able to offer you the personal touch you’ve been looking for. Our goal is to make all our students and their families happy. 

At Victoria Children's Group, we understand that for the majority of our students this is their first experience in a school setting.  Our passionate staff want to make sure that your child has the best care and a positive experience towards learning in school.  

Our experienced and dedicated teachers create an environment that supports and develops a love of learning, cooperation and respect for others.  They will implement a child-centered, age appropriate curriculum that focuses on fostering your child's social, emotional, physical and academic skills.    

Our goal is to offer your child a nurturing environment that will allow them to enjoy learning and develop necessary skills to move toward independence as they enter elementary school.

name: WEE CARE CHILD CARE
detail: Wee Care Child Care welcomes children from ages six weeks through five years. Our center is licensed by the Department of Health and Mental Hygiene and we take pride in our creative learning programs. These programs are grounded in teacher-guided activities based on monthly themes, with modifications based on age group. Our teachers work on developing and modifying routines for infants, providing language development for toddlers, and teaching the fundamentals of art, math, and science for preschoolers. Our caregivers seek to establish active communication with parents in order to design a program for your child in which he or she can thrive, experience the world, learn, and grow. In addition, our staff members are trained in CPR and First Aid.

name: WEE ONES CLUB, LLC
detail: The Wee Ones Club Preschool strives to generate educative experiences for our students that both increase confidence and independence while nurturing and supporting our young citizens.  Our goal is to create an environment where each child enters with the knowledge that they are respected and valued by their peers and teachers.  The tender age that our students begin preschool is honored by our staff.  Our classrooms aspire to be free of judgment and dedicated to providing every individual with the materials and guidance that make their first educational discoveries meaningful and lasting.

name: WEST 83RD STREET PRE-SCHOOL
detail:
Each year Goddard Riverside serves more than 3,000 children and youth through school-based, after-school, evening and weekend programs. The majority of children and youth in our programs come from low-income families who live in the surrounding neighborhood. Our programs provide safe, structured activities and the chance to interact with positive role models. We also engage whole families by offering information, encouragement and support to parents.

As a multi-service settlement house, we can give young people the continuity they need. Some children begin by attending one of our preschool programs and stay involved with us during elementary, middle, and high school. It is common for parents to have been in our programs as children, and we are often engaged with extended family networks.

name: WEST HARLEM COMMUNITY ORGANIZATION INC. HEAD START
WEST SIDE MONTESSORI SCHOOL
detail: Since our inception in 1963, we have been dedicated to providing an exceptional early childhood education within a warm and diverse community. We do this by combining key aspects of Montessori education with the best practices of current child development research, and by actively involving parents in the educational lives of their children. By encouraging their natural curiosity in an atmosphere of respect for self and others, we help children build a lifelong love of learning and a strong foundation for becoming self-directed learners, flexible thinkers, creative problem solvers, resilient individuals, and empathic citizens of the world.

name: WONDERFUL QUALITY TIME, INC.
detail:
WQT, Inc. believes that in order for children to grow and develop into productive individuals the must be nourished and supported. The job of our staff is to provide an atmosphere the fosters learning through activities that stimulate, motivate as well as challenge the efforts of children entrusted to our care.

Activities will be provided to enhance both gross and fine motor skills. We are committed to enhancing, encouraging and promoting literacy and language acquisition in our children. We take particular pride in building self-esteem and self-sufficiency through self-awareness of ones abilities. We vow to work closely with young children as facilators in assisting them in achieving success with socialization skills and academic performance.

Our desire to be on the same page with all persons that service and provide care
for our children is of the utmost importance. Conferencing with parents and other professionals will take place on a regular basis and/or as needed at all times.
We pledge to make every child a priority.

name: Y A I/N Y L GRAMERCY SCHOOL & ROOSEVELT CHILDREN'S CENTER
detail: Our preschool for children with special needs is located in the heart of Manhattan. We offer a full range of therapeutic services, and a language-based curriculum.Our student and staff population is culturally diverse and two of our classrooms are designed to serve Spanish speaking children and their families.

name: Y M/Y W H A OF WASHINGTON HEIGHTS AND INWOOD
Y W C A POLLY DODGE EARLY LEARNING CENTER
YORK AVENUE PRESCHOOL
detail:
The mission of York Avenue Preschool is to provide the whole child with the foundation for growth in all developmental domains.  Young children learn best in a structured, supportive, nurturing, engaging environment through hands-on-experiences.  Each child’s curiosity is embraced to facilitate cognitive, social-emotional, and physical growth.  Our exceptional teachers provide classroom environments that foster engagement and love of learning.

York Avenue Preschool welcomes our families to be partners in learning.  Parents are involved in all school functions, classroom celebrations, parent-teacher conferences, and all Parent Association sponsored events.  The fulfillment of our school’s mission is complete with the involvement and participation of all of our parents.

name: 4 ANGELS DAY CARE INC. - INFANT PROGRAM.
detail:
Our personal philosophy of education begins in a child centered environment in early stages of development where the only work a child has is meaningful exploration and play. This play will promote the social, emotional, physical and cognitive development of every child involved and will be done in an inclusive setting that promotes multicultural, non-sexist and non-stereotypical experiences, nutrition, personal hygiene and safety.

We encourage, respect and acknowledge the fact that every child is an individual that learns at his/her own pace and in his/her own way. We give these children love and attention and the opportunity to make choices according to their own individual preferences and curiosities. Our philosophy and practices adapt according to changes in the educational process and the children’s needs. We take pride in what we do, for example:

P = Providing guidance to children in getting along with one another, learning together and providing new and challenging learning experiences.

R = Remembering to keep the program flexible and provide a lot of positive reinforcement.

I = Interacting with children, parents and the community in order to foster mutual respect.

D = Demonstrating respect for cultural and ethnic diversity and modeling positive behaviors.

E = Encouraging independence while still giving lots of comfort and love.

name: BIG BIRDS PLAYHOUSE CORP.
detail: Big Bird play house has been serving parents in Staten Island since 1991. Providing them with the safe environment where children feel loved, respected and safe. This is a place where they learn and will grow building a foundation for their future. We believe they can learn from play, stories, arts and crafts at their daily centers. All of our staff is warm and caring to each child’s specific needs. This will give them the confidence they need to feel good about themselves and to love and respect one another.

name: BIG BIRDS TODDLER TIME
detail: Big Bird play house has been serving parents in Staten Island since 1991. Providing them with the safe environment where children feel loved, respected and safe. This is a place where they learn and will grow building a foundation for their future. We believe they can learn from play, stories, arts and crafts at their daily centers. All of our staff is warm and caring to each child’s specific needs. This will give them the confidence they need to feel good about themselves and to love and respect one another.

name: BUMBLEBEES-R-US INFANTS
detail:
Early Childhood Education is a science that we take seriously. Every aspect of our curriculum is designed is to target each area of development. However, our children just think that they are here to play and sing and have FUN!

We believe in a Whole Language Approach; we surround the children with language. This type of program helps the children to develop a lifelong love and appreciation for literature as well as an early understanding of language structure. Through a variety of activities based on the alphabet, even our youngest children learn to recognize letters and their corresponding sounds. They develop skills in listening, speaking, observing, thinking and ultimately reading and writing. Science, math and social studies are integrated within the reading program, as well as creative art, music, dramatic play and a variety of gross motor activities.

In addition, our center integrates other methodologies that allow children to develop “multiple intelligence” We seamlessly incorporate the guidelines of CDA certification standards, Universal Pre Kindergarten programs, Head Start programs, NAEYC, and Board of Education guidelines.

name: BUSY BEACH DAY CARE CENTER - P/S
CASTLE DAY CARE INFANT/TODDLER
detail: Castle Day Care believes children learn and develop in a secure, loving environment. Since we are concerned with the whole child, we aim to balance their development in all areas: social, emotional, physical and intellectual. Our staff needs to be dedicated to helping children grow at their natural pace by building self-confidence, strengths and skills.

name: CASTLE DAY CARE II
detail: Castle Day Care believes children learn and develop in a secure, loving environment. Our staff needs to be dedicated to helping children grow at their natural pace by building self-confidence, strengths and skills.

name: CASTLETON HILL MORAVIAN PRE-SCHOOL
detail: At Castleton Hill, we welcome families of all religious and ethnic backgrounds to become a part of our preschool family. Here, your child will be nurtured and treated like the special individual that he or she is as they learn skills vital to a successful future. Skills such as, how to work alone and with others, share and take turns, express thoughts and ideas, listen to others and develop feelings of security as they discover the world around them. Together by working and playing, we will build an important educational foundation and create a love for learning—all while having fun!

name: CHILDREN AT PLAY EARLY INTERVENTION CENTER
detail:
Children At Play’s mission is to provide each child with a unique and individualized educational, therapeutic experience which will lay the foundation for their future as capable and productive adult members of their community.

Children At Play’s objective is to use the professional guidance of our caring staff with the most up-to-date professionally recognized treatments, to encourage each child to attain his/her full developmental potential.

Equally important, Children At Play is committed to educating parents to understand and advocate for the special needs of their children throughout childhood, adolescence and adulthood.

name: CHILDREN'S HARBOR MONTESSORI SCHOOL
detail: "Guided by the essential Montessori Philosophy, the Children’s Harbor Montessori School provides an art-centered curriculum which empowers children to use their creative thinking for the best possible development of their individual, cognitive, and emotional selves."

name: CHURCH OF THE HOLY CHILD PRESCHOOL
ELITE DAY CARE LEARNING CENTER
detail:
We welcome you and your child to explore and discover our resourceful environments, experienced teachers and innovative curriculum unlike any other. Elite Day Care Learning Centers remain committed to providing your child with an unsurpassed learning and nurturing experience.  Embark your child within Elite's Advanced PreK Program to maximize their literacy competence and widen their academic success for the upcomong elementary years.
Our full day schedule contains additional academics that accelerates and enhances their performance.  Education is fun while making new friends and building strong relationships with teachers who partner with families to cultivate the development and well-being of every child. Elite Day Care's age-appropriate programs provide unlimited opportunities for stimulating your child's learning potential.

detail:

name: EXCEL PRESCHOOL INFANT/TODDLER PROGRAM
detail:
Choosing a preschool can be an exciting but overwhelming experience.  There are many factors to be considered when choosing the school that is right for you and your child.  At Excel Preschool, we consider it a privilege to have your child as part of our wonderful family. 

Our teachers and staff work tirelessly and are commited to nurturing the whole child. 

Our mission in educating young children comes from the belief that each child has his own unique characteristics and special interests. Each child is encouraged to explore his surroundings in an engaging, fun and creative atmosphere, while acquiring early academic and social skills. 

Please explore our programs, as well as our Universal Pre-K. We believe you will find a program that will be a perfect fit for your child.  We welcome you to  visit or call us at any time.

name: GATEWAY DAYCARE
detail: At Gateway Academy, our focus is on your child! We view each child as a Promise deserving every opportunity to realize his/her full potential. The dream of each child is personal: to become that artist, lawyer, nurse, teacher, physicist, pilot – already visualized in the child’s mind. Our responsibility is to provide the best possible launch pad for that dream to become a reality. This is a responsibility we take very, very seriously.

name: HIGH HOPES OF S. I. INC / INFANT/TODDLER
detail:
Each child has the right to be respected for his or her feelings, needs, abilities, uniqueness, and culture. In order to truly respect a child, one needs to know what is basic to a young child’s development. By assisting a young child to develop a sense of trust, autonomy, and initiative, a solid foundation is laid for his future healthy growth.
 A young child is eager to accept new experiences as wonderful and exciting adventures when they are presented to him in a way that is natural for him – through play. When provided with opportunities to initiate play, in an environment in which he feels valued, loved, respected, and accepted, the child is able to learn and master new skills, and to develop those characteristics which will enable him to meet life’s challenges: self-esteem, confidence, self-discipline, the belief that he can have an effect on his world, a love of learning, intellectual curiosity, creativity, empathy, a respect for the rights of others, an acceptance of those who are different from himself

name: HUGS & KIDDIES OF STATEN ISLAND,NY LLC
detail:
Hugs & Kiddies Early Learning Center offers child care services to the Staten Island, NY area. With over 10 years of experience, we provide full and half day service and late hours to ensure that your child receives the care that fits your busy schedule.

Our professionals plan activities and games to ensure that your child will learn and grow in a loving environment with personalized care and plenty of attention.

name: HYLAN DAY CARE
detail:
At Hylan Daycare, Inc., our mission is to offer every child with a quality and unforgettable early childhood learning experience. Our focus is to provide a nurturing, safe, stimulating and developmentally appropriate environment centered on each child’s individual needs. We believe that stimulating our children’s young minds to think critically and solve problems through play-based and aesthetic activities will inspire them to use their intuition, imagination and creativity toward understanding something as a whole.

Composing the musical tale of a lively childhood adventure is what we strive to paint your child’s day, everyday. Hylan Daycare, Inc. is staffed with early childhood education specialists, teachers, and child caregivers who have a deep understanding of the child’s mentality and at the same time open-minded to the dynamic changes that take place while the young brain undergoes rapid development during the early years of life. We are an independently-run and locally owned day care center, licensed by the New York City Department of Health and Mental Hygiene and highly compliant with the statutory and national standards for quality child care.

Hylan Daycare, Inc. is a child-friendly day care center. We use positive discipline in cultivating desirable behavior,genuine praises, and continuous motivation. On top of that, our staff are fully-mandated reporters by the state of NY, which means we are entitled and are given the lawful right to report to the authorized officials any incidences or child report of abuse, injurious punishment, or coercive treatment.

name: IVY LEAGUE EARLY LEARNING ACADEMY
detail:
We have built our program around the understanding that each child is unique and that we cater to the individuals, not just to groups. Our curriculum will constantly be evolving, as time passes our students will have the exposure to lessons that are relevant to what is going on in our community, nation, and the world.

We place an equal amount of importance on keeping our center family oriented. In doing so, we create bonds with children and parents that last long past when they leave our program. By creating these bonds it allows us to give each child the tools they need to be successful.

name: J & J ACADEMY
detail: J & J Academy Preschool offers an academic curriculum within a flexible framework in which social development and educational skills are learned. Our school strives to provide a simulating and secure environment where children enjoy learning and take pride in their accomplishments. The goal of our school is to make learning an exciting and rewarding experience while instilling in the children basic skills and values. J & J Academy strives to make the nursery school experience a happy time filled with adventure, discovery and growth.

name: JEWISH COMMUNITY CENTER OF STATEN ISLAND
detail:
The JCC of Staten Island is dedicated to encouraging harmony throughout the community by providing facilities and programs that are open to all regardless of race, religion, creed, color, national origin, sex, age, disability, marital status, sexual orientation or political affiliation. Everyone is welcome at the JCC.

When the Jewish Community Center of Staten Island opened its beautiful bronze doors on Victory Boulevard in 1929, its mission was to provide a home for the Jewish community for social, recreational and educational activities where people of all races and religions would feel welcome. The standard for excellence and inclusion continues to this day and it is truly a center for the Jewish community as well as a community center for all.

The JCC’s growth through expansions and new sites paralleled that of the borough – from the North Shore to the South and then to mid-Island. New programs were developed to serve the needs of the community such as day camp (1932) to preschool (1960), from the Dorothy Delson Kuhn Music Institute to Kosher Meals for the Homebound Elderly to First Foot Forward, a preschool for children with special needs.

We have a core of dedicated volunteers and staff that assist in enhancing your experiences here: from taking an exercise class to enjoying a cultural event, from celebrating a holiday to stretching your mind. This is your Community Center and membership is open to people of all races, religions, ethnic backgrounds and financial circumstances.

Mon. – Wed. – Fri. 7am – 6pm
    Tues. & Thurs. 7am – 9pm
    Saturday closed
    Sunday closed

name: JEWISH COMMUNITY CENTER OF STATEN ISLAND@ SMILES AROUND US
JOAN ANN KENNEDY MEMORIAL PRE-SCHOOL (SETON FOUNDATION
KID SMART- A LEARNING CHILD CARE CENTER
LITTLE STAR PRESCHOOL
detail:
Little Star was created to provide your child with the necessary skills to succeed in a fun, nurturing environment. The warmth and experience of our teachers will ensure that your child’s day is filled with not only excitement, but also learning and an appreciation of our Jewish heritage.

Our curriculum was prepared by an experienced team of educators. Our goal is that, upon graduating from our program, your child will have a firm grasp of the alphabet, colors, and numbers. In addition to the core curriculum of the State of New York, we will cover world events, nature, feelings, and our Jewish heritage. Our playground area is furnished with optimal equipment to ensure your child’s physical development.

As a licensed facility, safety is a number one priority at Little Star. The classroom, playground, and all supplies were designed with your child’s well-being in mind. Our teachers are trained in emergency care (First Aid, CPR, etc.). Regular safety exercises are incorporated into the curriculum.

We welcome parents as active participants in their child’s education and are delighted to discuss anything that might concern you during the school year.

We look forward to working together to provide your child with a fun, exciting, and successful preschool experience!

name: MINI WORLD PRESCHOOL
detail: Mini World Preschool is a community school providing services for Staten Island for 25 years. Our goal is to provide a developmentally appropriate program within a nurturing environment, enabling children to develop their social, emotional, physical, and academic skills, resulting in a positive attitude toward learning. We offer a child friendly environment, a fun outdoor play area, licensed and certified teachers, nurturing teachers and teacher assistants with an enriched learning program. Come in and tour our school. By the way, we offer free universal Pre-K for 4-year old children. Mini World Preschool has been a Universal Pre-Kindergarten provider for the past ten years.

name: OAKDALE ACADEMY INFANT TODDLER PROGRAM
detail:
Our program is designed to foster creativity and independence, while promoting academic enrichment through a specifically designed, curriculum utilizing challenging and stimulating materials and teaching methods.

The program cares for the child as a whole so that there is also emphasis placed on nurturing emotional growth, while sparking excitement and enthusiasm in learning endeavors.

Children work in small groups based upon their abilities rather than arbitrary chronological grouping rules. This ensures each child being able to work at his own pace and reach his own potential through opportunities for critical thinking and problem solving. Small grouping by ability allows us to respond to individual needs.

At Oakdale Academy we believe that each child is entitled to reach his or her full potential both as an academic learner as well as a well-rounded individual. We carefully attend to the academic development while nurturing the emotional growth and self-esteem of the child. Our goals include:

    Successful transition from home to school
    Development of self-esteem
    Development of respect for others and the environment
    Development of self-confidence
    Appreciation and love of learning
    Positive feelings towards school
    Critical thinking skills
    Critical evaluation
    Critical observation
    Logical problem
    Analysis and synthesis
    Ability to work within a group and independently
    Ability to make choices, inquiries and observations
    Ability to process information and a variety of modalities
    Ability to recall, retain and utilize information

name: OAKWOOD HEIGHTS COMMUNITY CHURCH NURSERY SCHOOL
PORT RICHMOND DAY NURSERY HEAD START
RICHMOND HILL CHILDREN'S CENTER
detail:
Richmond Hill Children's Center is licensed by NYC DOHMH. We have been offering
daycare, preschool, and summer camp programs to the Staten Island community since 2004. In addition, RHCC has been a NYC DOE authorized free Universal Prekindergarten Program provider since 2008.

Our mission is to provide the opportunities necessary for our students to have fun and make the most of their skills in a safe and secure environment. At RHCC, we believe that the preschool years are the most impressionable time in a child's life. Therefore, it is important
to use this developmental period as the foundation that will help them
to succeed in later school years and throughout their lives.

Our curriculum is designed to stimulate healthy growth in all areas of a childs development. RHCC is family owned and operated and is open year-round from 7am – 6:30pm and prides itself in providing quality services.

name: SMALL WORLD PRE-SCHOOL
detail: Welcome to Small World Preschool of Staten Island, NY! Our school has been providing nurturing children in Staten Island since 1977. We also offer childcare services because your children deserve nothing less. For all your preschool and childcare needs, Small World Preschool is the name to trust.

name: SMILES AROUND US FOR INFANTS AND TODDLERS, INC.
SOUTH SHORE TODDLER ACADEMY & PRE-K
detail: We offer a certified Pre-K program authorized by the New York City Board of Education along with Pre-School, daycare and learning center. Our three classrooms are staffed by certified teachers and instructors. Working parents leave their children from 3 to 6 years old in a secured, safe, and healthy environment. Special Children events like graduation and holiday parties are held in our Ballroom or main room which accommodates 200 people Our center is open from 8:00 AM to 6:00 PM, Monday to Friday servicing the needs of the children.
business hours: 8:00 AM to 6:00 PM, Monday to Friday

name: STATEN ISLAND EARLY CHILDHOOD CENTER
detail:
We are the preschool professionals in the area, providing high-quality, center-based care and early childhood education for children from 2 to 6 years old. Our well-trained staff consists of teachers who will give your child the personal attention and guidance they will need to learn as they relate to the world around them. Children can learn their ABCs, numbers, colors, music and other group activities that help them prepare for the future. Our classrooms are also equipped with computers so your children can prepare for the future.

Through years of experience in preschool education, the capable staff at Staten Island Early Childhood Center has learned that, through individual attention, your child can spend their preschool years having fun learning at their own pace to make an easy transition into their school years. All of the teachers there are totally committed to providing tender loving care to each and every child so that parents can rest assured that their child is in a well-balanced, happy environment.

Call Staten Island Early Childhood Center and help your youngster take that first important step! If you're interested in a creative, individualized program geared to your child's social, emotional, physical and cognitive development, we are the preschool professionals to see!

name: STATEN ISLAND MENTAL HEALTH HEAD START
STATEN ISLAND MENTAL HEALTH SOCIETY HEAD START
STEPPING STONES PRESCHOOL
detail: Mission: To educate students to become competent, independent thinkers and lifelong enthusiastic learners with respect for themselves and others. We strive to provide a safe nurturing environment, filled with open-ended age appropriate materials for exploration and discovery. Our hope is to offer challenging thematic curriculum with a commitment to the education of the whole child. Education is a social process. Teachers and children are expected to experiment collaboratively to form conclusions. We strive to create an environment, which will bring out the innate passion for learning that is in each child. We provide purposeful experiences that create cooperation, care, respect, exploration and participation. We believe that every child is different and learns at his or her own pace. Children learn by doing. Hands-on experiences are well remembered.

name: TANGLEWOOD MONTESSORI SCHOOL
detail: Tanglewood Montessori DBA The Tanglewood School provides enriching education for young children in the Staten Island, NY area. Each student of the Tanglewood School is treated as an individual. All students are encouraged to become self-motivated, independent learners. We provide a nourishing environment, prepared to meet the needs and desires of each and every child.

name: THE CHILD STUDY CENTER OF NEW YORK/BEST FRIENDS DAYCARE
THE CHILDREN'S CENTER
detail:
The Children's Center provides quality child care and early childhood education programs for children of students at the College of Staten Island. The Center offers an infant/toddler program, a universal prekindergarten program,
a preschool program, and a school age program, all featuring hands on learning experiences in a caring, well-supervised environment.

The Center is licensed by the New York City Department of Health, Bureau of Day Care, and is sponsored by the College of Staten Island Association, Inc. All child care programs are partially supported by state and federal funds. The Universal Prekindergarten program is funded by the New York City Department of Education. The availability of these programs is contingent upon continued funding by these sources.

name: THE GINGERBREAD LEARNING CENTER
detail: The Gingerbread Learning Center in Staten Island, New York, is an environment designed to strengthen the developmental milestones that your pre-school child has difficulty with by building on those that have already been mastered.

name: THE VILLAGE PRE-SCHOOL
detail: At The Village Preschool we are a Reggio Emilia style education inspired preschool program. We build partnerships with our parents and provide our families with a program that is designed to be flexible enough to meet each family’s unique needs, while delivering a high quality preschool curriculum.

name: THE WONDER YEARS PRESCHOOL INC
detail: The Wonder Years Preschool of Staten Island, NY has been offering excellent early childhood education since 1990. We take pride in our custom built state of the art facilities, N.Y.S. certified teachers, CPR certified staff, and 3 beautiful outdoor play yards and free universal Pre-K programs for 4 year olds.

name: THE WONDER YEARS PRESCHOOL, INC.
detail: The Wonder Years Preschool of Staten Island, NY has been offering excellent early childhood education since 1990. We take pride in our custom built state of the art facilities, N.Y.S. certified teachers, CPR certified staff, and 3 beautiful outdoor play yards and free universal Pre-K programs for 4 year olds.

name: UNITED CEREBRAL PALSY OF N.Y.C. INC. S.I CHILDREN'S PROGRAM
VOLUNTEERS OF AMERICA STATEN ISLAND EARLY LEARNING CENTER
WAGNER COLLEGE EARLY CHILDHOOD CENTER
detail: Welcome to the Early Childhood Center for Preschool and Kindergarten at Wagner College. Our individualized program meets the needs of young children with opportunities to explore, imagine and discover.  Enrollment is offered to children on Staten Island and surrounding communities.

name: A CHILD'S PLACE PRE SCHOOL
detail: "We are the people who nurture children and partner with families to provide a healthy upbringing. No one, but no one, can offer a home away from home as well as we can. We want you to think of us as nurturers, educators, and partners."

name: A NEW DAWN ELEMENTARY & PRE-SCHOOL
detail:
We are an independent, co-educational school serving a diverse student population in Queens, New York.

A New Dawn School provides exciting learning opportunities from Pre-school through 6th Grade.

Our traditional school calendar runs from September to June. A New Dawn also offers full-day summer programs from July through August.

A New Dawn believes that the humanity of each teacher is vital if young people are to learn well, for it is from human understanding that a community of trust and understanding is created and maintained.

name: ABC EARLY LEARNING CENTER OF BAY TERRACE
ABC KIDDIE LAND DAY CARE CENTER
ABC PRESCHOOL
detail:
ABC Preschool & Kindergarten Center Corp. is a leading private provider of early childhood care and education in Queens. We are licensed by the City of New York and completely meet the requirements and high standards of the Health, Education, Building, and Fire Departments.

Everything we do at ABC Preschool & Kindergarten Center involves early childhood development. We provide a dynamic program and fully qualified staff, as well as the highest level of customer service for each family. With our exceptional student to teacher ratio, we are able to focus on the needs of each individual child. Our newly renovated, modern, luxurious, state of the art facility with indoor gym, spacious outdoor fenced in playground is the basis for a happy , friendly, nursery school and Kindergarten community giving children a positive, solid foundation for their school careers, and the rest of their lives.

name: ABC PRESCHOOL & KINDERGARTEN CENTER

name: ADVENTURELAND CHILD CARE CENTER, INC. PRESCHOOL
ALL CHILDREN'S CHILD CARE
detail: All Children's Child Care offers a creative curriculum that's tailored to your child's age and needs. We provide developmentally appropriate activities including computer use, writing, library time, art, music, and games. Plus, we go on weekly trips to help your child experience more of what our community has to offer. Summer camp is also offered for kids ages three to 12 years.

name: ALL CHILDREN'S CHILDCARE (INFANT/TODDLER)
detail: All Children's Child Care offers a creative curriculum that's tailored to your child's age and needs. We provide developmentally appropriate activities including computer use, writing, library time, art, music, and games. Plus, we go on weekly trips to help your child experience more of what our community has to offer. Summer camp is also offered for kids ages three to 12 years.

name: ALL MY CHILDREN DAY CARE
detail:
Our Philosophy. Learning, curiosity, and motivation are natural and ongoing processes in children’s growth. We encourage children to be aware of the environment and appreciate the things around them. Our staff creates an atmosphere wherein these qualities are nurtured and encouraged.

Our philosophy is framed by the lens that each child is a seed; just as the sun provides warmth, the rain provides water and the soil provides the nutrients to feed and nurture each seed, thereby realizing and cultivating the seed into its potential bloom, we believe we must provide the nourishing and responsive environment to cultivate fulfillment of each child’s individual qualities and abilities, and then marvel as they bloom!

All My Children Daycare and Nursery School is a nursery and preschoolbased on various philosophies and principles.Thesephilosophiesencourage learning conditions that enhance thinking and experiential learning, tailoring the environment to accommodate children’s needs, and implementing a curriculum that is guided by children’s interests, in an eco-friendly way. We believe thatchildren, their familiesand societyall benefitfrom a high quality, early childhood program in conjunction with an eco-friendly surrounding and that there is a critical link between a child’s early experiences and latersuccessesinlife. It is our goal to provide all of our children with the best possible education delivered by motivated, inspirational teachers who have been specially trained to teach an integrated curriculum.

Our education is a response to the needs of children today, hoping to root their learning in authentic experience and scaffolding their growth through a higher order thinking processes.

This will render self-awareness and a heightened sensitivity to being citizens in a culturally diverse world. Particularly, as the world is extended beyond natural borders to virtual ones, self-awareness must be linked to promoting leadership qualities, directed towards effective judgment of how to use the gift of one’s natural freedom to prepare for a better tomorrow.

This environment will be created by materials and resources that are open ended,with  teachers and staff who are continuously growing as learners through professional development and a life-long appreciation of learning.

Our warm and eco-friendly early childhood education centers offer green building details such as abundant daylight , toxic-free paints and finishes, and Energy-Star appliances. Our toys, furnishings, and supplies have been explored and considered to bring the best in learning and earth-friendly materials.  Eco Friendly diapering? Absolutely!  Organic,  locally-sourced food? Absolutely! Green cleaning practices and an eco-friendly curriculum? Absolutely! We wouldn’t have it any other way!

Through an interdisciplinary curriculum, focusing on developmentally appropriate practices and world consciousness, to build skills and concepts, as well as continuously maintaining a close partnership with parents and community, the teachers will inspire, support, love and nurture each of ALL MY CHILDREN.
