name: ANGELS IN THE GARDENS CHILD CARE CORP
detail:
With our knowledge and expertise, ANGELS IN THE GARDENS Childcare center has created an environment that encourages your child's confidence, self-esteem, manners and sharing ability during these joyous and challenging years.

Our teachers and staff in the classroom are facilitators and nurtures, providing children with age appropriate activities, encouragement and support. Our staff is always close at hand with guidance and assistance. We also encourage children to help themselves. Our children learn and develop best in a secure loving clean environment.

Our teachers and staff are dedicated to helping children grow at their natural pace by building self-confidence, strength, and skills. Our program also offers a small teacher child ratio!

name: ASTORIA BLUE FEATHER HEAD START
detail: Astoria Blue Feather Head Start, (ABF), located in Astoria, Queens, has been providing high quality services to children and their families for over 15 years.  The preschool was recently awarded the Gold Certificate of Excellence by the Administration of Children and Family Services/US Department of Health and Human Services.  ABF educates 58 children in inclusionary classrooms and ensures high teacher to student ratios in all instructional settings.  Classrooms include young learners receiving Special Education services, as well typically-developing children, from the local Astoria community.  As a Head Start program, Astoria Blue Feather is unique among AHRC New York City preschools.

name: BABY STEPS
detail: Our mission at Baby Steps is to teach children life skills that go beyond reading, writing, and math. Playing with toys helps develop motor skills and teaches lessons about sharing with friends. Singing songs while washing hands instills an interest in the arts while forging social bonds and educating children about the need for good hygiene. Each activity is designed with a specific lesson or outcome in mind.
business hours: Monday to Friday – 7:30 am to 6:00 pm

name: BETH GAVRIEL DAY CARE CENTER, INC.
detail:
Beth Gavriel DCC has been operating since 1996 and it is a part of a true multi-cultural Jewish communiy in Forest Hills, Rego Park, Queens. The center provides day care services from 8:00 AM to 5:00 PM Monday-Friday for children two to six years of age and our staff are professional and certified teachers.

We offer various activities such as music, art, jamboree, drama, and computer.The day care is also open during the summer in July and August for our summer program. The summer program includes trips, entertainment, swimming pool, parties and then some!

We also provide for the older school age children an after school achievement program. This program offers homework help, computer instruction, creative art projects, music, dance, outdoor activities, buddy help and friendship.

name: BETH JACOB JEWISH ED. CTR
detail: At Forest Park Preschool everyday is an educational, fun, and lively day. In our safe, caring environment, your child  will be encouraged to reach  his or her potential. Our experienced and nurturing staff will allow you peace of mind to know that while your child is in our  school he/she is receiving the best care, emotionally, socially, and academically. This site will inform families of our programs and future events.

name: BIRCH FAMILY SERVICES INC
detail:
Birch Family Services is a team of more than 3,000 teachers, therapists, social workers, psychologists, nurses, residence counselors, administrators, board members, and family members working together:

    To provide the finest education, habilitation, and residential services to people with autism and other developmental disabilities
    To help their families overcome the lifelong obstacles they face in raising children with disabilities.

We’ve grown from a few classrooms into a large network of schools, residences, and family support programs located throughout New York City. Committed to sharing our expertise widely for the benefit of those we serve, we train hundreds of professionals throughout the tri-state area in our Birch Training Institute.

name: BLANCHE COMMUNITY PROGRESS DAY CARE CENTER INC.
detail: Blanche Community Progress Day Care Center, Inc. is licensed and registered in the state of New York to provide day care services. We consider it a valuable role in the community to be entrusted with the care of children. We work with parents in creating a childhood experience for kids that promotes development physically, emotionally and intellectually. The Day Care environment also gives kids a place to practice and hone their social skills.

name: BLANCHE COMMUNITY PROGRESS DCC #2
detail: Blanche Community Progress Day Care Center, Inc. is licensed and registered in the state of New York to provide day care services. We consider it a valuable role in the community to be entrusted with the care of children. We work with parents in creating a childhood experience for kids that promotes development physically, emotionally and intellectually. The Day Care environment also gives kids a place to practice and hone their social skills.

name: BOOKS & RATTLES INC., II
detail: We are community-based childcare centers that provide optimum care for children in an environment of guidance love and support. We provide numerous educational programs at our four sites located in the neighborhoods of Middle Village, Elmhurst, Holliswood and Queens Village. Our curriculum is play based with innovative  state of the art classrooms. We believe that families are an integral part of a successful childcare program. Through family involvement we are better able to meet the development and personal needs of children. We like to think that families and childcare centers can and should work together to provide an environment that facilitates the growth of a child into a physically and emotionally healthy individual. Every child deserves to learn and have fun doing so.

name: BOOKS & RATTLES PRESCHOOL
detail: We are community-based childcare centers that provide optimum care for children in an environment of guidance love and support. We provide numerous educational programs at our four sites located in the neighborhoods of Middle Village, Elmhurst, Holliswood and Queens Village. Our curriculum is play based with innovative  state of the art classrooms. We believe that families are an integral part of a successful childcare program. Through family involvement we are better able to meet the development and personal needs of children. We like to think that families and childcare centers can and should work together to provide an environment that facilitates the growth of a child into a physically and emotionally healthy individual. Every child deserves to learn and have fun doing so.

name: BRIGHT BEGINNINGS IN QUEENS VILLAGE, INC.
detail:
Bright Beginnings in Queens Village, Inc. is a not-for-profit child care center located on the grounds of Creedmoor Community Campus in Queens Village.  We are licensed by the NYC Department of Health to offer full-time, educationally based child care for children between the ages of 8 weeks and 5 years.  Our hours are 6:45 a.m. through 6:30 p.m., Monday through Friday, and our enrollment is ongoing throughout the year, with priority enrollment and sliding scale fees offered to New York State employees. Available child care slots not filled by NYS employees are offered to community families.

We also offer a, free, 2 ½ hour Universal Pre-K for 4 year olds who turn 4 by December 31st each year in conjunction with the NYC Department of Education.
business hours: 6:45 a.m. through 6:30 p.m., Monday through Friday

name: CAMBRIA CENTER FOR THE GIFTED CHILD.
detail:
Cambria Center for the Gifted Child started as a home-based school back in 1980 with a group of four children that were participants in the Founder/Director’s doctoral research project. In 1982, Cambria Center for the Gifted Child moved into its own building and expanded to include not only pre-school but also elementary school. As the word spread, the student population grew and have continued to succeed based upon our theories concerning education.

The Center has grown to become a pre-eminent private non-sectarian educational institution with an annual enrollment of nearly 300 students from pre-k through 5th grade. A great number of our graduates leave our institution and enter preparatory schools on academic scholarships, while others enter some of the more challenging public schools and are raised a grade level based upon their academic strengths. Cambria Center for the Gifted Child attributes its success not only to its focused, caring approach to education; but also to it’s staff, families, and those within and outside of the community that have supported us.

name: CAMBRIA HEIGHTS CHRISTIAN ACADEMY
detail: It is with great pleasure that I welcome you to Cambria Heights Christian Academy website. Thank you for your interest in our school. We take pride in our accomplishments and welcome the opportunity to provide your child’s with quality holistic education and a successful early childhood experience. We look forward to working with you and your child.

name: CENTER OF EXCELLENCE II QUEENS VILLAGE, INC.
CENTER OF EXCELLENCE SPRINGFIELD GARDENS PRESCHOOL
detail: Academy of Excellence and Center of Excellence Child Care Center's program has been developed to serve the needs of today's family. We answer the dilemma that many parents face...where to find quality child care. As teachers and care givers, our goal is to achieve a sense of continuity between home and center. We believe it is important for children to maintain a familiar and comfortable routine. Through parent/teacher communication, we individualize each child's care and learning opportunities. As a family oriented child development center, our child care center's assures a quality "home away from home." We provide an atmosphere where children are respected, staffs are responsible, and parents are always welcome.

name: CENTRAL QUEENS Y EARLY CHILDHOOD
detail: The mission of our organization is to sustain and enhance the quality of family and individual life for all members of our community regardless of age, gender, religion, ethnic or cultural background, national origin or disability, within an environment that fosters Jewish values, culture, learning, identity and continuity.

name: CHABAD EARLY LEARNING CENTER
detail: Chabad Early Learning Center is a place where young children receive an exciting, creative, and nurturing early learning experience. We provide children with the building blocks to grow educationally, socially, and spiritually. Each child receives a well-rounded enriching education, filled with Torah and tradition intertwined with a wide array of secular academic subjects.

name: CHARLES R. DREW EARLY LEARNING
detail:
Our mission is to inclusively enhance the lives of our students and their families. The center is dedicated to providing a safe, developmentally appropriate environment to all preschool children. Our focus is to provide a stimulating early childhood experience, which promotes each child's social/emotional, cognitive, language, and physical development. We appreciate the differences found amongst our families and our colleagues. We are committed to providing an environment in which diversity, distinction and merit are affirmed, celebrated and enhanced.

The scopes of services at CRDELC are comprehensive. They include education, recreation, socialization, music and dance, health services, physical examinations and follow-up, speech therapy, physical and occupational therapy, psychological examinations, nutritional services and referrals to myriad of community and support services for our children and their families.

CHILD DEVELOPMENT CENTER AT QUEENS COLLEGE

name: COLONIAL CHURCH NURSERY SCHOOL
detail: As a ministry of the Colonial Church of Bayside, the Nursery School seeks to serve children in the name of our Lord Jesus Christ who said, "Let the little children come to me... for the kingdom belongs to such as these." Understood in its broadest sense, this ministry brings all enrolled children a day-to-day experience of God's love in their relationships with the staff, in their personal growth and in their play.  Within a distinctively Christian setting, the Colonial Church Nursery School hopes to assist parents in the total nurturing of their children by encouraging the mental, emotional, physical, and spiritual development of each child entrusted to our care. In that spirit we welcome children from all backgrounds.

COSMOKIDZ INFANTS
detail: We have full and half day learning programs for newborn infants, toddlers, preschoolers and pre-kindergarteners. Located conveniently in the center of Fresh Meadows, Queens, we have a brand new facility with bright, spacious classrooms and a private enclosed rubber-padded playground. We are NYC DOH certified and our teachers are NYS DOE approved.

name: CRAYON BOX PRESCHOOL
detail:
The Crayon Box Preschool believes in giving children a foundation of education they can take with them throughout their student years. Preschool is the first place these young students are exposed to a school setting. We have a program that is both welcoming and fun, while stressing the fundamentals of preschool learners.

Our preschool is set up in centers with specific functions in each. These centers enrich children’s senses and allow for many mediums for learning. The children can explore these areas on their own during free time and also have teacher guided times in each.

The daily routine is set up to make children feel secure in knowing what will happen next. When children feel safe and secure in their surroundings, they are free to accept new ideas and concepts.

With all of these factors at work, the students of The Crayon Box Preschool will receive a well rounded education by a professional and dedicated staff.

The school offers a flexible schedule to fit YOUR needs and is payable in monthly installments for your convenience. We look forward to meeting you and if you have any questions, please feel free to contact me at 718-888-9341.

name: DCAIB CENTER
detail: Day Care At Its Best!!! Serving the Rosedale Community for over 9 years... 4 programs... 3 locations!!! (Nursery* Preschool* Afterschool* Summer Program)

name: DIKI DAY CARE
detail: Our goal is to provide the safest and happiest environment that will give our children every opportunity to develop to their greatest potential under the caring eyes of our experienced teachers. Our little students will build skills and confidence through games, songs, movement and art. Our teachers provide an outlet for creative expression by encouraging children to play in our child-directed centers to ensure that a child develops at his or her own pace. Sharing, cooperating and taking turns teaches a child the importance of being a team player.

name: DIKI DISCOVERY CENTER
detail:
We are delighted that your child will be attending the Diki Discovery Center. We are very proud of our program and look forward to having your family become part of our pre-school family.
The Diki Discovery Center is a place where Toddlers and preschoolers engage in discovery of the properties of materials and items in their environment. No one can paint a picture of a house before discovering that paint is wet, that it drips, and that it can be spread with fingers and other tools. They need repeated experiences before they are able to use materials symbolically. For example, one cannot build a train with blocks without an understanding that blocks are hard, solid, can be stacked or might fall over if they are not held steady, At Diki Discovery Center; children have many opportunities to pursue in‐depth investigations of materials around them. Our values reflect our belief that children learn best in a rich environment that focuses on the interweaving of cognitive and creative ways of thinking and learning. Our staff is truly committed to working in partnership with you and your child to provide for the highest quality early childhood experience.
I look forward to getting to know both you and your child and sharing a rewarding preschool experience.

name: DOLLY & FRANK RUSSO SR. FIRST STEP EARLY CHILDHOOD CENTER
EMILIA'S KIDS
detail:
Emilia’s Kids is a comprehensive Early Childhood Development Center centrally located in Middle Village/Elmhurst, Queens.  EMILIA’S KIDS BELIEVES IN SOCIAL AND EMOTIONAL LEARNING.  We offer DAYCARE SERVICES, FREE UPK, FREE EARLY INTERVENTION SERVICES, and FREE DOE approved speech therapy, physical therapy and occupational therapy to the 0-21 population.

The core of our philosophy has always been “It Takes A Village.”   We have been working with children at this center for over 17 years, providing them with individualized therapy programs in a triad framework of therapist, family and child. We believe in supporting families throughout their various transitions through their child’s educational journey. Our staff of speech therapists, occupational therapists and physical therapists readily interface with social workers, psychologists, service coordinators, special educators, and many other professions in the best interests of each family and the child’s development.

OUR CENTER IS ENGAGING SOCIAL AND EMOTIONAL LEARNING IN OUR CLASSROOMS.

name: FIRST STAR DAY CARE LEARNING CENTER - INFANT/TODDLER
FOREST HILLS JEWISH CENTER NURSERY SCHOOL AND KINDERGARTEN
detail:
The Forest Hills Jewish Center provides a complete, well balanced, secular and Jewish education. Our educational methods encourage children to become confident, independent, responsible, and creative thinkers. We integrate our secular studies (language arts, science, music, math) and art activities around the Jewish calendar.

Active learning is the cornerstone to our educational approach. The children participate in exploratory activities that use all their senses; touching, smelling, tasting, seeing and hearing. Using their five senses, the children actively explore and experience their world in a fun and sometimes messy way.

Children are also exposed to pre-reading activities on a daily basis. The presence of visually supportive materials encourages early literacy.

Equally important as active learning is the development of interpersonal skills that will help ensure smooth and productive in the years of learning that lie ahead.

name: FOREST HILLS MONTESSORI
detail: The mission of Forest Hills Montessori School is to provide both creative and stimulating intellectual, artistic, and developmental experiences for children ages 3-12. We strive to cultivate each child's natural desire to learn and to foster his/her natural curiosity and love of knowledge. We are committed to providing a rigorous, classical education that focuses on scholastic achievement. Emphasis is placed on core skills in reading, writing, and mathematics, using a broad repertoire of teaching techniques and technologies. These skills are enhanced by their integration throughout the curriculum. Our faculty creates experiences that foster critical thinking, problem solving, and collaboration. Our educational philosophy is centered on intellectual, physical, and artistic development. Forest Hills Montessori School's size and low student-teacher ratio enable our exceptional faculty to maximize individual attention. Our nurturing, family-oriented environment brings out the joy of learning in each child.

name: FOREST HILLS NURSERY AND KINDERGARTEN
detail: The purpose of this establishment is to provide for the education of pre-school children. We accept children ages 2-5 years old.  We will seek the social, emotional, and intellectual development of the child.  Pre-school children are at a stage in their lives where a major growth of their intelligence occurs; therefore this is the TIME to give our children a positive foundation that they will have for their future benefit.

name: FOREST HILLS WEST SCHOOL
detail: Our school is located on a tree-lined street directly across from Juniper Valley Park, in the lovely residential neighborhood of Middle Village, Queens, where many teachers and students live. Classrooms are fully equipped and our state of the art outdoor play area is safe and age appropriate. Each child benefits from a program individually tailored to promote their physical, social, emotional and cognitive development.

name: GOOD FOUNDATION PRESCHOOL
detail:
The goal of Good Foundation Academy For The Gifted Child is to produce happy, intelligent, well-adjusted children. Here you will find a nurturing, educational environment for children of ages 6 weeks to 12 years. Classes include infant, toddler, preschool, kindergarten,and after-school programs.

We recognize that each child has unique talents, learning styles and personalities. Our highly qualified teachers and staff are committed to working within each child’s comfort zone to ensure optimal social, emotional and educational results. Classes are kept at a low student-teacher ratio and often fill up quickly.

name: GRACE CHURCH PLAYSCHOOL
detail: Serving Whitestone for over 40 years, the Grace Church Playschool provides children ages 2 ½ through 4 years old with a safe learning environment where they develop primary skills such as working with numbers, colors, shapes, and the alphabet. Play is an essential component of the program including both indoor and outdoor games as well as music and movement activities. There is a 5:1 ratio of students to teachers and our educators are world class. Please call the director, Michele Anderson, at (718) 767-2162 for information or to register your child.

name: GRYC LITTLE STARS PRE-SCHOOL
detail:
The mission of the Greater Ridgewood Youth Council (GRYC) Inc. is to improve the quality of life for youth and families throughout Western Queens.
As a not-for-profit 501(c)(3), non-sectarian organization that continues to serve youth since 1980, the GRYC is a leader and participant in ongoing efforts in educational, recreational, cultural and employment programs that help youth find new avenues of learning and positive life experiences.

name: HAPPY BEES DAY CARE
detail:
We are one of the happiest, friendliest places in Astoria for families with children from three months to five years old.  At Happy Bees Day Care, we strive to make every day a learning day filled with new and wonderful experiences to help young leaners find what interest and inspires them.

It is our joy and pleasure to help families find just the right early education setting for their children and we’re sure it’s here with us, in a safe and comfortable place where learning is full of fun.
business hours: Monday Through Friday 7:30 a.m. to 6:00 p.m.

name: HELPING HANDS CHILDREN'S DAY CARE CENTER, INC.
HOLLIS HILLS JEWISH CENTER NURSERY SCHOOL
detail:
The Hollis Hills Jewish Center Nursery School provides a cheerful, warm, safe and caring environment where young children up to age 5 years old are encouraged to grow emotionally, socially and academically. We integrate language arts, math, science, music and art with the Jewish calendar.

All of our teachers are certified and we are licensed by the New York State Department of Health.

name: HONEYPOT DAY CARE, INC.
detail:
HoneyPot Daycare located in Flushing, NY was founded in 2011.  HoneyPot of Flushing was created with certain goals in mind.  We believe that a combination of Eastern and Western philosophies of education will highly benefit all children and produce the most well rounded students.

To achieve our goals, we start by making sure that every child is and feels safe, comfortable and happy in their environment.  If a child’s needs are not met, or they are not happy to be a part of our HoneyPot community, learning will not take place.  The child must be well cared for, respected, and guided into positive learning experiences.

Once the child’s needs are met and they have developed a positive self-image, we use a combination of instructional methods and cooperative learning to build the foundation of your child’s education.  Their education begins with patience.  Patience is a skill that is taught and continuously worked on.  It is a crucial element in becoming a lifelong learner.

The teachers also work on community building.  Teaching children how to share, take turns and care for one another.  We want our children to be aware of their surroundings and to express themselves freely.

During lessons, children are taught to concentrate and to not disturb the class without raising their hands first and waiting to be called on.  They are taught persistence and encouraged not to give up. However, care is taken to ensure that the child is not to pushed past their frustration point.  To ensure this, developmentally appropriate activities and lessons are tailored to each age group and can then be modified to accommodate each child as an individual learner.

Ultimately, we want to produce students that are happy, healthy, academically prepared, patient, emotionally and socially confident and ready for kindergarten!

name: HOUR CHILDREN INC.
detail:
Founded more than 25 years ago, Hour Children® was named to acknowledge the important hours that shape the life of a child with an incarcerated mother – the hour of their mother’s arrest, the hour of their visit, and the hour of her release.

The organization’s vision is to end the cycle of intergenerational incarceration.  Our mission is to help incarcerated and formerly incarcerated women and their children successfully rejoin the community, reunify with their families, and build healthy, independent and secure lives. To accomplish this, Hour Children provides compassionate and comprehensive services and encourages all to live and interact with dignity and respect.

name: I BEAR DAY CARE CENTER
detail:
Children are exposed to many subjects such as English, Korean, Spanish, Numeracy, Literacy, Language Arts, Science, and Social Studies. Children love the challenge of learning something new every day because it involves their surroundings and real life skills. Children never feel overwhelmed as subjects are rotated daily, lessons are accommodated for students’ various learning styles and levels, and individual review is provided daily.

iBear’s mission is to help our community by preparing future bright leaders with the latest education and the warmth and intelligence of our dedicated, devoted, and NY State certified teachers.

name: ICCD
detail: ICCD was founded in 1986 with the mission of assisting preschoolers with disabilities and their families. In September, 1994 ICCD was selected as a recipient of a New York State Education Department grant to initiate the development of a Special Class in an Integrated Setting (SCIS). Currently, ICCD is a leader in integrated programming with twenty SCIS's operating in New York City and Nassau County. Additionally, we have self-contained classrooms in our Bayside and Rego Park facilities. ICCD was awarded the first New York City contract for Universal Pre-Kindergarten (UPK) services and have been providing UPK classrooms since the programs inception in New York City. Our innovative approach has made ICCD as leader in education. We utilize a developmentally appropriate curriculum that supports the New York State Learning Standards. All aspects of our program are child-centered and geared to involve and incorporate families. Special attention is given to designing a classroom environment that is divided into learning centers. Each center is stocked with a rich variety of materials, equipment and tools which are accessible to the children.

name: IMAGINE EARLY LEARNING CENTER @JAMAICA KIDS PRESCHOOL
detail:
Vets Kids, serving children ages 2 months to 5 years, is a nurturing learning oasis within a busy urban community located in the VA/New York Harbor Health Care System. Our four joyful, child-centered classrooms provide a unique and fun learning experience for each child.  Our new, state of the art playground includes age appropriate play areas for infants, toddlers and preschoolers.  We enjoy inteactions with the hospital and veteran community including fun and educational visits from doctors and other hospital professionals and support staff.  We participate in Memorial and Veterans Day parades and veteran appreciation activities. Come visit us at Vets Kids - where the excitement of New York City inspires our children to learn, grow and most importantly, imagine.

Since 2012 we have been contracted with the New York City Department of Education as a Universal Pre-K program for four year olds, focusing instruction on Kindergarten preparation aligned with the New York State Common Core Learning Standards.

name: INTERNATIONAL NURSERY SCHOOL
detail: The International Nursery School is a non-profit, multi-ethnic, non-sectarian nursery school servicing approximately 60 children. Dedicated to the healthy development of children, the International Nursery School epitomizes cooperation between home and school and between people of many ethnicities and cultures. We strive to form attitudes of acceptance, which will build better communities in a better world.

name: IVY DAY SCHOOL
detail: Welcome to a place of books and blocks, music and dance, art and creativity; a place filled with smiles and hugs and an abundance of good conversation. Ivy Day School is the right place for kids. We opened our doors to serve children and families in 2003. In each classroom, from Toddlers to Pre-Kindergarten, our highly skilled teachers provide the environment and experiences from which children learn and grow. At Ivy Day School, we recognize how important new beginnings are in each child’s development and to each family. Our mission is to provide a caring and nurturing environment where children can thrive academically and socially. Come visit us at one of our locations today! Ivy Day School aims to provide quality education to preschool-aged children to soundly prepare them for the adventures and rigors of formal education. We envision that all children, when given the proper guidance, setting, and instruction, will develop the necessary skills for a lifetime of achievements. Ivy Day School also strives to cultivate a supportive community between teaching staff, children and their respective families through open communication and extracurricular involvement.

name: JACK & JILL NURSERY SCHOOL II
detail:
At Jack & Jill Schools learning is a dance between the “teacher” and “learner.”  The “teacher” takes on the role of observer and facilitator.  She makes careful observations of the child and designs learning experiences to match the child’s motivation and unique level of interest.

More importance is placed on having adequate time to explore a topic as deeply as the children care to.  As our preschoolers take ownership of the learning process there is a powerful sense of confidence that develops in them that will set the stage for future learning.

Children leave here with a sense of confidence, robust curiosity about the wonderful world we live in and a sense of ownership of their learning experiences.

JDC/JCS is an agency committed to servicing a diverse group of children, ranging from typically developing children in our UPK program to children with significant special needs.  At JDC / JCS, staff works together as a team, ensuring that each child’s individual academic, social and behavioral needs are met. name: KID KRAZY EARLY CHILDHOOD DEVELOPMENT CENTER.
detail: At Kid Krazy we understand the search for your child's first school can be filled with anxiety. You are not only seeking a place where your child can learn and develop, but more importantly, a place where your child feels safe, secure and loved. We believe there is nothing more important for a child than to have a positive self-image. Once a child feels secure in their environment, learning becomes a natural process. At Kid Krazy all of our teachers understand that children are born with a huge capacity to learn. Our children are given the tools to stimulate their natural curiosity and to develop a strong sense of empathy and respect for one another. The children's days are filled with play (to develop creative imagination and social skills) as well as fostering early reading, writing, math, science and art skills. Our goal is to bring out the best in your child and to nurture their love of learning.

Our program is filled with fun experiences for children.  Experiences that become memories of their childhood and will build their future.

name: KIDZ VILLAGE, LLC
detail: Kidz Village welcomes children ages two through five to its brand new private early education center. With that in mind, we have created an environment that incorporates the Reggio Emilia philosophies, as well as the Montessori philosophies.

name: LIC YMCA EARLY CHILD CARE PROGRAM
LITTLE APPLE PRESCHOOL
detail: At Little Apple Preschool, we believe that active learning is best achieved during play. That's why our curriculum is based on exploring and discovery all the while enjoying our day! Though all our activities are created for learning and expanding what we already know, we can't forget how important TLC is. Your children become our family and we provide the best care for them- just as you would. Who said that a hug can't help you learn? There is no better way of learning than hands on- dirty hands that is! We believe that the world around us is the best plateau for understanding how everything works and is connected. Taking in the outdoors and realizing that we are one with nature is how we learn best!

name: LITTLE ELMS CHILD CARE CENTER,P/S
detail:
Bright Horizons is the world's leading provider of employer-sponsored child care, back-up care, education and work/life solutions with more than 700 child care and early education programs and schools for employers and working families across the US, UK, Ireland and Canada. Committed to creating great work environments for its 18,000 employees, the company has been named 12 times as one of FORTUNE magazine's "Best Companies to Work for in America."

Bright Horizons provides work/life solutions for more than 800 leading employers to help them address challenges across key life stages. Programs include child care, back-up care, college counseling, elder care, and work/life consulting.

The first few years of life are an extraordinary time that sets the stage for all the years that follow. Our program for learning creates educational environments that empower children to be confident, successful, lifelong learners and socially responsible citizens. Bright Horizons' innovative programs help children, families, and employers work together to be their very best.

We promise to greet you with open arms and a warm smile each and every morning.

I promise to support you, encourage your creativity and to appreciate your dedication to the children, their families and to me.
I promise to listen to you, value your insights and to work with you so that we will always cherish the warm, nurturing environment that defines Little Explorers.

name: LITTLE TOTS RED WAGON
detail:
Little Tots, proudly serving the community for 11 years.

We believe that play is a child's work. We provide a safe and nurturing environment for children to engage on a social, emotional, physical and cognitive level. Children learn to separate from their parents through a gentle process of adjustment, and come to love the routines, risks, excitement, challenges,and independence of school.

We are excited to be a part of the Universal Pre-K program which is provided free of charge by the Department of Education. Our classrooms are open and playful environments, led by phenomenal teachers, where children move freely to interact with each other. We believe children learn best through a combination of play and teacher-directed activities, and we help children to develop friendships as they learn.

name: LITTLE WONDERS, INC.
detail: We provide evaluations of your child's development in the areas of speech and language, fine and gross moter, social-emotional, cognitive, and adaptive skills. Evaluations are provided at no cost to families upon referral to the local school district and parental informed consent. The child is assessed in all areas of development to determine strengths and weaknesses. A social history, psychological evaluation, speech and lanquage evaluation, occupational therapy evaluation, physical therapy evaluation, an educational evaluation, and hearing screening are performed to assess your child's development. If a delay that warrants remediation is found, your child may receive programs and services as recommended by the committee on preschool special education.

name: LOLLY'S LEARNING CENTER
detail:
We promote moral, emotional and intellectual independence, enabling children to meet and exceed their individual goals. Parents and Teachers work together to set unique and individual goals for each child. Children are respected and empowered. Head Teachers hold Master of Science degrees in Early Childhood Education or a closely related field. Learning is CHILD-INITIATED and goals are set based on each child’s unique needs and individual pace. SMART BOARDS and teacher aides technologically enhance your child’s learning experience.At LOLLY’S we practice an Open Door Policy. Families and parents are welcome to walk through at ANY time. Parents are encouraged to be an integral part of their child’s education, through parent teacher conferences, and volunteering in the room. We offer small group classes in yoga, martial arts, photography and music. Lolly’s follows the standards set up by the National Association for the Education of Young Children. Children are EMPOWERED to make their own choices. All Staff is certified in Child CPR and First Aid Classroom Learning Areas are stocked with the highest quality, eco-friendly furniture, manipulatives, literacy tools, libraries and art materials.

Lolly’s Little Learners excel in the following LEARNING DOMAINS:
ALL play is centered around a thematic curriculum.
Creative Expression – Phonetic Awareness – Language Development – Mathematical Thinking
Scientific Thinking – Socio-Emotional Development – Physical Development – Continuity & Transition
Peer Modeling, Lively Interactions and Conversation are essential parts of the curriculum.
Learning Environments provide children with opportunities to INVESTIGATE, REPRESENT and SHARE.

name: MONTESSORI PROGRESSIVE LEARNING CENTER
detail:
Montessori Progressive Learning Center is a non - profit organization that has been serving the community since 1989. We are committed to providing a safe nurturing environment for the educational growth of children.

A Montessori approach is described as an “education for life.” Our priority goes beyond the development of just the child’s academic skills. Children are taught to become self-confident, independent thinkers, interested in the world, and enthusiastic about life.

Our Progressive Learning approach is designed for our Afterschool and Summer Camp Programs. Each child is given the opportunity to grow through academic enrichment, physical activity and social peer interaction. A stimulating environment is created to allow your child to go beyond their perceived limitations and to reach their greatest potential.

Montessori Progressive Learning Center admits children without regard to race, color, religion or national origins.

name: NEW MILESTONE DAY CARE CENTER
detail: In 2007 New Milestone was created with the mission of providing preschoolers with a safe, nurturing environment in which to grow and learn. Our program incorporates all content areas including: Art, Music, Science, Math, Social Studies, in addition to Social Emotional components. All areas are adapted and modified to meet each child's individual needs. We believe that a child's greatest tool in the creation of self is their play. Through play, children are able to actively explore, manipulate, investigate, interact, create, discover and take risks. Children are endowed with a natural curiosity about their world. With the manipulation of concrete materials children can develop new understandings about their environment, relationships with others as well as their experiences.

name: NEW WORLD EDUCATIONAL CENTER
detail:
New World Educational Center is a non-profit, nonsectarian, private nursery through second grade center.  We were founded in 1980 to provide quality day care for working families.  We strive to provide our children with a warm, nurturing environment.  We facilitate learning and foster self-esteem by creating opportunities for children to explore, create, experiment, interact, problem solve and communicate freely.  We welcome students of every race, color, national or ethnic origin.

We are licensed, monitored and inspected by New York City Department of Health and Mental Hygiene.  We are also accredited by the New York State Department of Education.  We participate in the ACD Voucher Program and HRA Begin Program.

Our curriculum promotes the linguistic, social, emotional, cultural and social development of all our children.  Activities are learner-centered and help promote a child’s independence and self-confidence.  Our curriculum is in alignment with the NYC core balance literacy and core balanced mathematics program.

Progress reports and/or reports cards are handed out three times a year so that parents can check their child’s progress.  We encourage parents to be involved in the education process and participate in school activities.  We distribute newsletters which update parents on events at the center, as well as give them parenting tips on how to build a child’s self-esteem, boost language skills, teach responsibility, and build reading readiness skills.  The newsletter also provides parents with health and safety tips.

name: NEW YORK CHILD LEARNING INSTITUTE
detail:
The New York Child Learning Institute is affectionately known as "NYCLI" (pronounced "nicely"). It was founded in 1994 as a state certified nonpublic preschool for children with autism. In 1995, educational services were extended to school-age children between the ages of five and eleven. In 2002, NYCLI was certified to serve the needs of learners up to age 21. The institute implements a science-based educational approach and is committed to providing the highest standard of education for its students.

The educational services offered by the institute include center-based and in-home individualized behavioral intervention for children with autism. Autism is a pervasive developmental disability that is characterized by severe deficits in social and language development. With effective educational intervention, these children can learn critical language, social, and academic skills. As competencies in these skill areas develop, the children begin to build meaningful relationships with others and to live more productive lives.

The institute's educational model is based on the principles of Applied Behavior Analysis, which has been demonstrated to produce effective outcomes for children with autism. The application of this science-based educational model is enhanced by the warmth and dedication of the professional teaching staff.

Although it is an independent, nonpublic institution, NYCLI's preschool and school are accredited and certified by the New York City Department of Health and the New York State Education Department.

detail:
North Side School is an independent, non-profit charter school specializing in education and early childhood development. Here at North Side we understand that the early years are vital to the establishment of skills that will enhance the learning process for the rest of the child’s life. However, we are also aware of the various needs and learning styles of each child, and are able to implement the educational process to meet the needs of each child. We recognize that every child’s individuality must be respected and nourished.

Our highly trained staff of NY state certified teachers and assistants instill a thirst for knowledge which provides each child with a solid foundation, preparing them for their futures. We take pride in seeing and meeting the student’s personality and intellectual needs, rather than viewing them as part of the classroom process. It is our goal to instill a desire to learn and provide the surroundings to feed that desire.

We offer a Universal Pre-Kindergarten Program to those children that are turning four years of age, as well as after school programs for those who are interested.

If you would like to enroll your child in North Side School, or would like more information as to our curriculum and services, feel free to navigate this website. We will be sure to provide you with any additional information you may need.

detail:
On Our Way Learning Center helps children with developmental delays and disabilities reach their full potential through a wide range of therapies, education, and other interventions provided by our team of skilled and licensed professionals.

Known for our multicultural diversity and integration, all of our programs are run based on the core values of respect and tolerance. Not only do we service students of many different races, cultures and religions, we also run a special education pre-school which integrates regular mainstream pre-school students into the same classrooms.

Open 12 months a year, our beautiful state of the art school is situated on 8.5 acres, located half a mile from the Queens / Nassau border. Our impressive campus includes two occupational and physical therapy rooms, classrooms, a computer lab, a music room, a gym, and a large enclosed outdoor play area, secure and inaccessible from the street, which contains a variety of modern playground equipment.

name: PAL WESTERN QUEENS EARLY LEARNING CENTER
detail:
PAL Head Start program serves 463 children, ages 3-5 and provides educational, social services, health, mental health, nutrition and parent involvement opportunities for the families of the children served. PAL Daycare programs serve an additional 390 children of working families annually. The day care programs serve children from 2 years old to 5 year old. Integrated with these services are Universal Pre-Kindergarten (UPK) programs which serve four year olds. Head Start and Day Care programs are funded by the Agency for Child Development of the city of New York.

After offering Early Childcare Education opportunities to families for more than forty years PAL continues to be one of the major providers in the City of New York. We operate four full time Head Start programs, three Day Care/Collaboration programs and two pure Day Care programs. Within these programs PAL enhances learning opportunities by providing inclusion/disabilities opportunities in three of the four Head Start programs. These programs also benefit from the consultancy of a Nutritionist, Mental Health sponsors and a Health practitioner. Each center is staffed with Early Education Professionals, who ensure that children are given the best early learning experiences coupled with appropriate developmental opportunities through dance and music programs. The children attending the programs are served nutritious meals daily through the Child and Adult Care Food Program (CACFP). This program provides monies for all children who attend the program to receive meals that are child friendly and nutritious.The head start and daycare programs operate all year round, with hours varying from 8am to 6 pm. (Head Start 8:30 to 4:30 Day Care 8 to 6). Ms. Asneth Council is the Director of the Childcare and Nutrition. Ms. Elisa Gordon-Douglas is the Manager of Food Programs.

name: PARENT PLUS OF ST. ALBANS
detail:
Our mission is to "Train up a child in a way that he should go, that when he's old, he will not depart from it". Prov 22:6
This provides the framework of a firm foundation on which they can continue to build their lives. We are open year round and accept vouchers. Children are taught letters, number recognition, shapes and colors, and dramatic play. Classrooms are bright and spacious. We also have a large outdoor play area. Our curriculum promotes social enrichment and high self-esteem. Field trips and nature walks supplement our daily learning experiences.

name: PARSONS PRESCHOOL
detail:
The mission of the Parsons Preschool is to provide a warm, caring, and stimulating early childhood environment that is safe and nurturing. It is a time of fun, warmth, security, exploration, and discovery. The school fosters self-esteem and builds confidence based on self-respect and respect for all others. We follow the “Golden Rule.” We have created a loving, trustful, and respectful environment which enables children to love, trust and respect their parents, teachers, each other, and especially themselves. We believe in the value of human diversity and the fair treatment of all people and the earth. Students and their families feel comfortable and welcomed at all times. We view the parents as partners in the education of their children and integrate them into our curriculum, as well as integrating into our community and becoming part of it.

Our staff is professional and knowledgeable about childhood development and early childhood education. We work collaboratively with our staff, parents, and the entire community to guide our students in their learning process. We have high expectations that are guided by the developmental needs of each child, with an understanding that many of our children have needs beyond that of learning essential skills; their needs are personal, pervasive, and affect them at every level of humanity. We follow standard pre-school curriculum guidelines and the New York State Common Core project. We focus on the whole child with developmentally appropriate quality education developed to meet the needs of each child. The Parsons Preschool maintains a progressive curriculum promoting learning the tools necessary to succeed in school and in life. We encourage and develop them physically, socially, emotionally, and intellectually while being part of a whole community. The goal is for students to enter Kindergarten with the necessary skills to succeed and promote lifelong learning. Our goal is to give each child the opportunity to succeed.

name: PEE WEE FOLKS
detail:
Established in 1981, Pee Wee Folks has been providing the children of many communities in Queens and Long Island, New York with a strong educational foundation in a warm and nurturing environment. We offer a high quality, diverse and developmentally appropriate curriculum for children ages 2 through 5 years of age. In our Roosevelt location we also offer an infant and toddler program in addition to our Pre-K Program.  We realize that educational trends change continually so we do our best to keep on top of those changes. Our curriculum is designed to align with the New York State standards for early childhood education. We believe that fostering a love of learning and a thirst for knowledge at an early age is the key to academic success.

This is the core of our educational philosophy.
Our schools offer year round program options. From September to June we offer a high quality preschool program with hours to accommodate our working parents. We also offer an after school program for students 5-12 years of age. During the Summer we offer a variety of camp options for your children. On site recreational activities including water play and "Theme" events fill your child's day with fun and excitement. Our traveling program options offer our older campers the opportunity to visit a variety of Summer fun spots throughout Queens and Long Island. Supervision is provided by our certified adult staff to ensure a fun, memorable and safe summer for all!

name: PICK WICK SCHOOL, INC./PICK WICK SCHOOL
detail:
Welcome to Pickwick School. Pickwick School is the oldest and most respected nursery school in Queens and provides care for children from 6 months to 5 years old . It was founded in 1941 by Murray and Miriam Singer, and is nestled in a very quiet neighborhood in Briarwood, Queens. Pickwick School is currently owned by Chiarina and Patrick Nolan. Chiarina has been a part of Pickwick School for the past 27 years, both as an educator and owner. Our goal is, and always has been, to provide children with a safe and nurturing environment that gives each child the opportunity to grow socially, emotionally and intellectually.  We believe that children become active thinkers and creative explorers when given an opportunity to learn by doing. Our classrooms are designed to include different learning centers filled with hands-on activities and materials for the children to explore throughout the day.

Pickwick School also offers Universal Pre-Kindergarten, which is sponsored by the NYC Board of Education and provides children with a free 2 and 1/2 hour program that prepares children for Kindergarten and beyond.

name: PLEASANT LEARN-N-PLAY CENTER, INC.
detail:
At Pleasant Learn~N~Play Center, our programs are designed to meet each child's individual needs, to foster development of intellectual and social skills and to provide a safe, nurturing environment. Our curriculum is based on the nationally recognized: Creative Curriculum®  The curriculum uses the latest approaches and techniques for working with children while implementing developmentally appropriate practices.

Pleasant Learn~N~Play Center prepares children academically, emotionally and socially for elementary school. Additionally, we believe play is a vital element in a child's learning experience. It is a medium for self-expression and an excellent time to develop their individual thinking processes. 

A child takes in more information between the ages of one to six than they do the remainder of their life. We know these formative years are critical to the development of your child's creative talents, positive self-esteem and enthusiasm for learning. Pleasant Learn~N~Play Center provides a safe, nurturing environment for your child to grow and develop character.

Our Center and Programs are here for you and your child. Our schedules is established with a busy family lifestyle in mind. Nourishing Meals are provided so parents have one less thing to do before they leave the house. We have a comprehensive Communication Plan that keeps you informed about your child's day and center events. Parental Involvement is important to your child and us, so please feel free to visit Pleasant Learn~N~Play Center and discuss our programs..

name: POSITIVE BEGINNINGS # 1
detail:
Positive Beginnings, Inc. is a special education preschool in the Queens area servicing children ages 3 to 5 years.

Located in both the Flushing and Middle Village areas, we are centrally located and easily accessible by major highways and public transportation systems.

Our nurturing environment caters to children with special needs, and their families to provide quality educational programs tailored to enhance the child's development.

detail:

name: PRE SCHOOL OF AMERICA
detail:
Preschool of America is committed to providing a safe, nurturing, and stimulating environment for young children. We provide enriching opportunities every day so students reach their full potential socially, emotionally, physically, and cognitively within the learning environment.

The play-based curriculum focuses on literacy, math, science, social and emotional skills, and physical development. Classrooms are designed to inspire young learners, capturing each child’s interests, ideas, and independence to encourage a growing awareness of self. We prepare students for on-going schools by continually monitoring their readiness for new learning challenges.

We believe that the strength of the program is in the dedication of the teaching staff. Teachers create a kind, caring atmosphere to foster imagination and creativity. We strive to create mutual respect and encourage daily communication between parents, teachers, and administrators. We believe parents are the most significant adults in a child’s life; therefore, our doors are open to parents at all times.

Preschool of America is an organization that values people: the children in our care, their parents, and our employees. We continually work to earn the trust placed in us and strive each day to be the best providers of early childhood education in the community we serve.
business hours: 8:00 a.m. to 6:00 p.m. Monday through Friday

name: PRECIOUS CHILDREN DAY CARE CENTER INC#2
detail:
The goal of Precious Children Day Care Center Inc. is to produce happy, intelligent, well-adjusted children. Here you will find a nurturing, educational environment for children of ages 2 years to 6 years. Classes include infants, toddlers, prekindergarten and kindergarten programs.
 
We recognize that each child has unique talents, learning styles and personalities. Our highly-qualified teachers and staff are committed to working within each child's comfort zone to ensure optimal social, emotional and educational results.
 
We guarantee that your child will receive the care they deserve.

detail: Preschool R' Us's mission is to provide a safe, caring, developmentally appropriate environment for our growing children. name: QUEENS CENTER FOR PROGRESS
detail:
For over sixty years, the Queens Centers for Progress Children’s Center has been providing superior services to families in the community. The Children’s Center’s dedicated and experienced staff provides children with a warm and caring atmosphere that promotes learning, bolsters self-esteem and improves social skills. The large, bright, well-equipped classrooms and recreational areas allow children space to grow and flourish.

The Children’s Center offers an array of options for parents of both typically developing (non-disabled) preschoolers and children with disabilities.

name: QUEENSVIEW NURSERY SCHOOL AND KINDERGARTEN
detail:
Queensview Nursery School & Kindergarten is a cooperative private school allowing parents the opportunity to participate fully in your child's education.

Attendance options to suit your needs: Half and full days, mornings and/or afternoon. Early (8:00 AM) dropoff. 5 days a week Universal Pre-K and Kindergarten, and a 6-week summer session is also available.

Our program consists of a curriculum based on sound educational principles for children ages 2.9 - 5 years. Small groups mean individualized attention from caring and experienced professionals. Indoor and outdoor activities. Safe and private playground.

Queensview Nursery School and Kindergarten is a non-profit organization. New York State Registered. NYC Board of Health Licensed. Our teachers are certified and experienced. Scholarships available to qualified applicants.

name: RAINBOW CHILD DEVELOPMENT
detail:
At Rainbow, we understand the importance of establishing a caring and trusting relationship with every child. That’s why your child’s days here at Rainbow will always start with warm hellos and end with loving goodbyes.

The early years of your child’s life are a time of tremendous development and learning. Our curriculum are specifically designed to cultivate children’s independent thinking, encourage their curiosity to learn, and support their physical development.

Here, at Rainbow, we believe in child-centered pedagogy or student-centered learning. Our program focuses on the children’s needs, abilities, interests and learning styles with the teacher as a facilitator of learning. We also strongly believe that young children learn best when they are provided with meaningful instructional experiences that build upon and connect with previous experiences in their everyday life. Hence, by relating math, science, social studies, and art experience to a child’s everyday life, the child will find the information much more interesting and stimulating. We strongly believe that a daily schedule of self-exploration and academic learning will help your child excel in the challenging world that she will face tomorrow.

We are thrilled to have two state-of-the-art centers in the culturally-diverse borough of Queens, NY, and we take pride in our bilingual educational programs. All of the children at our Flushing location are exposed to both English and Chinese instruction throughout the day. At our new Fresh Meadows location, we are also offering free Chinese and Spanish lessons in our programs. You will be surprised at how much your child will learn!

name: RAINBOW CHRISTIAN PRESCHOOL AND KINDERGARTEN
detail: Children are precious.  They need safe and caring environments where they can learn about the world, about their strengths and talents, and about how to get along with others.   We opened our doors in September 1987 with a handful of children, a part-time staff, and a commitment to serving the needs of a diverse community. Since then our school has grown to include Nursery, Preschool, Universal PreK (UPK), and an after-school program for children ages 2 to 7. Still, our original mission has remained the same:  to provide parents with a safe, loving and dependable place, where their children can discover the joy of learning and of community.

name: READY, SET, GROW!
detail:
Our educational philosophy in Early Childhood Education at Ready, Set, Grow! is guided by the basic knowledge that each child is a unique individual with differing needs. The growth and development of a child requires active and creative interactions with both teachers and peers in a positive child-centered learning environment. Children are nurtured in a SAFE, gentle, constructive, and caring atmosphere where their social, emotional, physical, and intellectual growths are encouraged. We support such an environment: where children will be able to build a foundation for a lifetime of learning and develop confidence, a healthy self-esteem, and sensitivity in a diverse world.

​

name: RED FISH BLUE FISH INT'L PRESCHOOL AND EARLY LEARNING CENTER, COR
REDEEMER LUTHERAN NURSERY SCHOOL
detail:
Located at 92-10 217 Street in Queens Village, we are a safe, fun loving and caring learning environment. We have been serving the Queens Village Community for over 10 years. We have both Nursery classes for our three year olds, and preschool classes for our four year olds. Our preschool class is a free half day program for all four year old children under the supervision of the Department of Education. All of our teachers are certified, and teacher assistants hold their teacher assistant certificate.

The school is run under the leadership of Mrs. Annette Valerio. She has been a preschool director since 1995, and has also been an elementary school principal. She has been in the educational field for over 35 years. Her doors are always open to anyone who would like to visit our school or has any questions about it.

Our program offers both half and full day programs September through June. We also offer a “Kindergarten Prep” program for students who are whole day. In July we offer a four week summer program. See the information page on this website for more information on all of our programs.

name: REGO PARK DAY SCHOOL
detail: The purpose of this establishment is to provide for the education of pre-school children. We accept children ages 2-5 years old.  We will seek the social, emotional, and intellectual development of the child.  Pre-school children are at a stage in their lives where a major growth of their intelligence occurs; therefore this is the TIME to give our children a positive foundation that they will have for their future benefit.

name: RENANIM ACADEMY PRESCHOOL
detail:
Our philosophy is to provide a stimulating, academic environment where children develop intellectually, emotionally, socially and spiritually--with the support and guidance of his teachers--so that the child can make his own discoveries and reach his own conclusions (often through trial and error)--in an atmosphere conducive to growth, self-esteem and confidence. Parents are asked to be involved with their children--whether it be homework or birthday parties or school functions on or about holidays or issues relating to young children-- because we believe that there is a TRIANGLE OF LEARNING in which child and parent and school are each connected one to the other. The parent can reinforce what the child learns in school; the school can reinforce family practices that occur in the home. The young child is intimately connected and dependent upon his parents and the school; and we want his first formal school experience to be a positive one.
We have a strong belief that children are equipped with a natural curiosity for learning and desire to challenge themselves. We promote students to explore and discover their environment through play based and experiential learning. Children use educational tools and manipulatives to understand basic concepts and skills, while improving hand-eye coordination, memory and development of gross motor and fine motor skills.
We are committed to promoting children’s sense of competence, creativity and awareness of others.

name: RIDGEWOOD PRE-SCHOOL CENTER
detail: Ridgewood Preschool Center is a non-profit, preschool program sponsored by the Ridgewood Presbyterian Church for children in our communities.  It is non-sectarian and welcomes children of various ethnic and religious backgrounds.  The school has been in existence since 1964; providing a warm, supportive environment in which the children can express themselves and develop their own individuality.  The emphasis is on the total growth of the child: socially, emotionally, intellectually, and physically.  The teaching staff works closely with parents exchanging insights from time to time on each child’s development.  Staff is always available for consultation with parents.

name: RISE & SHINE OF FOREST HILLS
detail: The goal of Rise and Shine of Forest Hills is to produce happy, intelligent, well-adjusted children through age-appropriate learning. Here you will find a nurturing, educational environment for children of ages 2-5 years. Classes include Pre-Kindergarten, SCIS and Daycare programs.Home and school are a child's two most important worlds. Children must bridge together these two worlds together everyday. If home and school connect in positive and respectful ways, children feel secure. We are here to help your family with your child's transition into our center and into the world. We develop skills as they grow to show: self confidence, enthusiasm for learning, social skills, wholesome attitudes, self-discipline and an organized approach to problem solving. Your child will discover that learning is fun, while making and building strong relationships with friends and with teachers who partner with you in your child's education. We recognize that each child has unique talents, learning styles and personalities. Our highly-qualified teachers are committed to working within each child's comfort zone to ensure optimal social, emotional and educational results. We are very proud of Rise and Shine of Forest Hills and believe there is no better center of its kind in our community. Please give us an opportunity to meet you and provide you with a tour of our facilities.

name: SAINT ALBANS MONTESSORI DAY CARE CENTER INC.
detail:
St. Albans Montessori Academy of Learning is a re-established Program. It was originally established in 1985 and re-opened Fall of 2013. St. Albans Montessori is rapidly growing program providing a traditional Montessori environment, enriched with art, music, movement, and the students will study three languages.


St. Albans Montessori Academy of Learning is seeking an experienced Primary teacher for the ages of 2-5 years of age. NYS Early childhood certification/AMI certification, AMS certification preferred.  Bachelor's or Masters degree in Early Childhood Development, Education or preferred.  Must be qualified to teach Birth to Kindergarten in New York.


Hours will vary. 10 month School program /2 month Summer program.  Scheduled Working Hours: 7am-6:30pm or 9am-3pm

name: SAMUEL FIELD Y-BAY TERRACE PRESCHOOL CENTER
detail: Our programs are designed to offer young children an opportunity to play, explore, and engage in multi-faceted activities. Professionally trained teachers facilitate children’s growth through dynamic educational experiences. We provide a caring atmosphere in which children develop and thrive intellectually, socially and emotionally and where families feel welcome.

name: SANDRA'S SUNFLOWER CHILD CARE, INC.
detail: The Vision Of Sandra’s Sunflower Child Care Inc. is to empower and enable the children of our community to attain a brighter future by providing them with a better start. Community participation and awareness are of vital importance to Sandra’s Sunflower Child Care Inc. As a result we have formulated an approach to childhood education that allows children to both interpret and influence their environment. We also offer a Holiday and a Summer Program.

name: SESAME SPROUT
detail:
Sesame Sprout, Inc. aims to prepare students to live successful, healthy and productive lives. We work to prepare them for later success in school and the larger diverse world community which awaits them. We work to build strong intellectual, emotional and social foundations for our students, never losing sight of supporting their joyfulness, creativity, spontaneity and love of learning. We dedicate ourselves to: developmentally-appropriate practices; individualization; nurturance; supporting the development of each student’s full potential; building competence and self-esteem in children; promoting pro-social skills and an appreciation of diversity. We work collaboratively with families and strive to ensure that our interventions meet the highest standards of professionalism and accountability.

Our children are provided with a high quality, early childhood experience in a very safe and nurturing environment. Our very high child/staff ratio ensures that each child will receive individualized attention when needed.

name: SHELDON R. WEAVER DAY CARE CENTER
SHOLOM DAY CARE INC
detail:
Our Curriculum:
**Emphasizes safety. Teachers choose only the activities that are appropriate for the children in their group, and supervision is a requirement.
**Provides consistency and a predictable routine, which is comforting to children. Children are relaxed and ready to learn when they can anticipate what is happening next. As children move through developmental milestones they need to practice skills at which they are successful. The variety of skill levels will vary greatly with any group of children, even those that are all the same chronological age. Activities may change or be repeated. We may spend fewer or more minutes on a specific activity; the daily/weekly routine is a guide.
**Includes open - ended activities and materials that build a learning community in the program. When materials can be used in a variety of ways, more children benefit. Activities that allow for multi-ages and multi-skill levels will include more children. Older, or children with advanced skills will be models for younger children or those who haven't yet attained the skill. Activities in this curriculum encourage children to work together, share, and be successful at their individual skill level.
**Encourages participation in two and three dimensional art, music, dramatic play, and creative movement. 
**Promotes multi-sensory experiences. Many opportunities are included in our activities that allow children to learn through touch, smell, taste, vision, and hearing. We know that children learn most when information is provided through all the senses.
**Invites exploration and discovery. The kits for fine motor and creative art include open - ended questions to promote thinking and problem solving. Our teachers model curiosity and wonder which helps children reach new levels of development and deeper understanding of concepts.

name: SMALL WONDER PRESCHOOL,INC.
detail: We provide evaluations of your child's development in the areas of speech and language, fine and gross moter, social-emotional, cognitive, and adaptive skills. Evaluations are provided at no cost to families upon referral to the local school district and parental informed consent. The child is assessed in all areas of development to determine strengths and weaknesses. A social history, psychological evaluation, speech and lanquage evaluation, occupational therapy evaluation, physical therapy evaluation, an educational evaluation, and hearing screening are performed to assess your child's development. If a delay that warrants remediation is found, your child may receive programs and services as recommended by the committee on preschool special education.

name: SOUTH JAMAICA CENTER FOR CHILDREN AND PARENTS, INC.
ST NICHOLAS PRESCHOOL

We are a certified program that abides by the codes set forth by the New York Dept. of Health. We are licensed to accept children aged two years and nine months through five years and six months. Our goal is to provide a creative and safe learning environment where every child is special.

name: STEPPING STONE DAY SCHOOL, INC.
detail:
SteppingStone Day School provides diverse, in-depth on-site and in-home services for children from birth to age 5, both with and without disabilities. Using well-tested methodologies, a passion for excellence, a highly trained staff and individualized programs, we allow families to engage in their children’s growth and education.
SteppingStone Day School's mission is to provide collaborative evaluation, education, therapy and family support services so that young children can develop to their full potential and join with their families and friends as vital members of the community

detail:

name: SUNFLOWER KIDZ DAY CARE
detail:
At Sunflower Kidz we want to help every child reach their full potential and experience a love of learning that will carry them through their lives.

We believe that given the opportunity, children can experience many different daily activities and situations to help them grow and build positive self esteem. By creating a warm and caring environment that fosters creative thinking, independence, and expression, children can build confidence in their learning ability and get ready to embrace learning as a tool for their lives.

Children have the ability to learn and absorb as much as possible throughout their lives however more learning occurs during a child's first five years than any other time in his or her life. We will work individually with each child by combining play with routine learning to help children develop their mind, body and spirit (inner self). Our goal is to bring out the educational best in your child while encouraging a life- long love of learning. 

In addition to serving as a trusted childcare provider, we view ourselves as a partner working closely with parents to enhance and expand your child's early learning experiences and promote healthy child development.

name: SUNSHINE DEVELOPMENTAL SCHOOL
detail: The goals of this program are to interact with children in a loving and consistent way in order to aide the development of a love for learning and a love for school. This provides the strong foundation necessary for creating our leaders of tomorrow.

name: TEACHING, LEARNING & CARING DAY CARE
detail:
Children learn through play, for this is how they explore their world.
A safe, nurturing, enriched environment, coupled with the consistency of the same care giver provides the security for a child to thrive, develop and grow. The unique setting of a center* type of environment in a family home combines the very best of both worlds.

name: TENDER YEARS DAY CARE
detail:
Children learn through play, for this is how they explore their world.
A safe, nurturing, enriched environment, coupled with the consistency of the same care giver provides the security for a child to thrive, develop and grow. The unique setting of a center* type of environment in a family home combines the very best of both worlds.

name: THE CHILD CENTER OF NEW YORK
detail:
The Child Center of NY reaches out across diverse ethnic populations to create a supportive, caring place for children and families at risk. For more than 60 years we have been a powerful presence in the community—transforming outcomes of lives in the margins.

Our more than 50 programs empower children to make good decisions… establish places of safety…help parents build skills to become better providers and nurturers…and make connections to the community through Early Childhood Education, Individual and Family Counseling, Child Abuse Prevention, and Youth Development. All of our programs—from daycare to crisis intervention—promote emotional wellness and secure attachments to parents and other adult caregivers.

name: THE CORNER SCHOOL
detail:
Our Philosophy
We believe that children learn best when they are actively engaged in meaningful exploration in our stimulating learning centers. The Corner School provides developmentally appropriate programs for our children's age and stages of development. Our purpose is to provide a warm, inviting and well equipped environment in which children feel welcome, safe and successful.
      
Our Mission
Our mission is to provide high quality early childhood education. Our program embraces children of all abilities. We encourage parents to be actively involved in our community. Our caring, nurturing and enriched environment fosters a love of learning and inspires each child to realize their full potential.

name: THE FIRST PRESBYTERIAN CHURCH OF FOREST HILLS
THE LITTLE DOLPHIN, INC.
detail:
The Little Dolphin School is dedicated to enhancing young children's intellectual, social, emotional, physical, and creative development. We do this in a warm, nurturing environment filled with appropriate opportunities for children to explore the world around them.

Children learn and develop differently. Our program is individualized, as well as based on themes designed to spark enthusiasm and creativity in young minds. Our curriculum is based on the New York State Standards of excellence.
business hours: Monday through Friday from 8:30 AM - 4:00 PM

name: THE LITTLE LEARNING CENTER
detail:
NYS Licensed Director and Teacher
Approved by NYS DOHMH
CPR and First Aid Certified staffs
Bilingual Chinese/English Program
Academic Enrichment Program includes writing, workshop, vocabulary, enhancement, and math.
Extra-curricular activities include art & craft, singing and dancing.
Special ESL instruction for new immigrants
Breakfast, hot lunch, and snacks provided
