name: THE NEW BUSY BEE LEARNING CENTER
THE TOTS LOT,INC..
detail:
We would like to welcome you and your child to the world of The Tots Lot Preschool. Here at Tots Lot we offer a world of fun, happiness and creative experience. Studies have found that learning improves when children are engaged in an enjoyable and meaningful activity. That’s why every curriculum includes a variety of intriguing activities that stimulates early brain development with a focus of play.

The programs are all designed to enhance the child’s creative thinking and self expression. We are more than happy to be part of your child’s most treasured years.

name: THERE IS NO PLACE LIKE HOME
TINY FOOTSTEPS CHILD LEARNING CENTER
detail: Welcome to Tiny Footsteps Child Learning Center’s website. Our center offers premier child care to children from twelve months to five years old. Tiny Footsteps is not just a daycare facility but also a complete child development center. We welcome you to visit our dynamic and fun environment to see for yourself why Tiny Footsteps is different ... how committed we are to quality care and intellectual child development education of your child.  Tiny Footsteps believes that each child deserves to grow and learn at his or her own pace. Tapping into each child’s amazement at the world around them to encourage them to learn and discover. Responsibility includes providing the tools and the environment that gives children opportunities to develop to their greatest potential. Tiny Footsteps strives to give each child enough space and time to do the things that make them laugh, learn, and have fun.

name: VIP - VERY IMPORTANT PEOPLE II DAY CARE CENTER
detail:
Our goal is to provide a loving, fun, educational environment to all children, by which they may develop their sense of speech, movement, interaction and expand their personality.

Our hope is to open doors for communication, higher learning experiences and be able to recognize that every new step, as small as it may be, is a step forward to a brighter tomorrow.

Our wish is to offer a safe and clean surrounding where every precaution is taken for the welfare and comfort of the children, as well as adults, therefore creating a comfortable setting every one can look forward to, every day.

name: VISITING NURSE SERVICE NY HOME CARE EARLY /HEAD START
detail:
Accredited by the National Association for the Education of Young Children (NAEYC), VNSNY’s Early Head Start and Family Programs teach young parents the skills they need to raise healthy, happy children.

The Early Steps Family Center, located in Rockaway, Queens, operates an Early Head Start and a Head Start Program. The programs serve 185 families, including pregnant and parenting teens, and their children from birth through age 5. Parents and parents-to-be can attend workshops in childbirth, breastfeeding and child development. We also offer an on-site GED program, literacy programs for parents and the Fathers First Initiative. Doulas are also available. Services are free of charge. (Some programs have eligibility requirements for participation.)
- See more at: http://www.vnsny.org/about-us/in-the-community/early-head-start-family-programs/#sthash.5Tj1bsPT.dpuf

name: WHITESTONE SCHOOL FOR CHILD DEVELOPMENT
detail: The Whitestone School for Child Development has been a leader in pre-school education since 1988.  We are licensed by the NYS Education Department and the NYC Bureau of Day Care.  We serve children 2.9-5 years of age throughout Queens and neighboring boroughs.  For over twenty years, the Whitestone School for Child Development has been providing developmentally appropriate educational and therapeutic services to children and families.  We invite you to tour our facility and meet our staff to learn more about our programs.

name: WOODSIDE EARLY CHILDHOOD LEARNING CENTER
detail:
PAL Head Start program serves 463 children, ages 3-5 and provides educational, social services, health, mental health, nutrition and parent involvement opportunities for the families of the children served. PAL Daycare programs serve an additional 390 children of working families annually. The day care programs serve children from 2 years old to 5 year old. Integrated with these services are Universal Pre-Kindergarten (UPK) programs which serve four year olds. Head Start and Day Care programs are funded by the Agency for Child Development of the city of New York.

After offering Early Childcare Education opportunities to families for more than forty years PAL continues to be one of the major providers in the City of New York. We operate four full time Head Start programs, three Day Care/Collaboration programs and two pure Day Care programs. Within these programs PAL enhances learning opportunities by providing inclusion/disabilities opportunities in three of the four Head Start programs. These programs also benefit from the consultancy of a Nutritionist, Mental Health sponsors and a Health practitioner. Each center is staffed with Early Education Professionals, who ensure that children are given the best early learning experiences coupled with appropriate developmental opportunities through dance and music programs. The children attending the programs are served nutritious meals daily through the Child and Adult Care Food Program (CACFP). This program provides monies for all children who attend the program to receive meals that are child friendly and nutritious.The head start and daycare programs operate all year round, with hours varying from 8am to 6 pm. (Head Start 8:30 to 4:30 Day Care 8 to 6). Ms. Asneth Council is the Director of the Child

name: YAI /NYL CLEARVIEW SCHOOL ANNEX
detail: Our school and annex are warm and inviting settings located in the heart of Northern Queens, serving a diverse population including Spanish, Chinese and English speaking families. We carefully assess each child at their developmental level so we can support their growth and help them reach their full potential. Through our TEAM approach we consider every aspect of a child’s life including the family’s needs and concerns.

name: YORK COLLEGE CHILD AND FAMILY CENTER
detail:
Located in a new building on the former St. Monica’s Catholic Church site. The center has eight classrooms, a Parent/Staff Resource Room, a food preparation area and offices. The program has been designed to meet the needs of student/ parents by providing affordable, flexible child care. In the future parents will be able to enrolled their children in different components of the program:

    Infant-toddler
    Preschool
    School age

Children will be assigned to classrooms by age and developmental level. The center is licensed by the New York City Department of Health and Mental Hygiene.

name: YWCA OF QUEENS EARLY LEARNING CENTER
detail:
Our philosophy at the YWCA of Queens Early Learning Center UPK is that children learn best by doing. This free program uses appropriate developmental materials so that children become active thinkers and creative explorers rather than passive learners. Our large classroom is designed to nurture children’s intellectual development, self-esteem, independence, cooperation, and creativity.

By following the New York State Common Core Curriculum, we create a framework of learning that allows children to explore and problem solve, that builds upon their prior knowledge and interests, and that fosters their desire to be self-motivated in the pursuit of learning.

Our experienced and qualified staff carefully listen, observe, and document children’s work and growth. We conduct our program using the guidelines set by the New York City Department of

Education, the Department of Health, and the ECERS program.

Some of our annual events are two parent teacher conferences, costume parade, three age-appropriate educational trips, vision screening, picture day, moving-on day and parent participation day. We encourage all parents and caregivers to participate in these events and to volunteer in the classroom.

We follow the public school schedule for most of the year with a few variations. All parents will be notified on a monthly basis of any events or school closures.
